{"term": "2010", "caseName": "Borough of Duryea v. Guarnieri", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/2010/09-1476", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - March 22, 2011", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/roberts6/oral_argument_audio/22294", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "We will hear argument first this morning in Case 09-1476, The Borough of Duryea v. Guarnieri.", "start": 0, "stop": 10.213, "duration": 10.21, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "hear", "argument", "first", "this", "morning", "in", "case", "the", "borough", "of", "duryea", "v", "guarnieri"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Ortiz.", "start": 10.213, "stop": 11.083, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["mr", "ortiz"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 11.083, "stop": 13.26, "duration": 2.18, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "In asking this Court to cabin Connick v. Myers' public concern requirement, Respondent would constitutionalize, under the Petition Clause, large parts of the law of public employee discipline, and thereby grant to public employees a broad constitutional employment right that private employees do not enjoy.", "start": 13.26, "stop": 31.907, "duration": 18.65, "cleanText": [["in", "ask", "this", "court", "to", "cabin", "connick", "v", "myers", "public", "concern", "requirement", "respondent", "would", "constitutionalize", "under", "the", "petition", "clause", "large", "part", "of", "the", "law", "of", "public", "employee", "discipline", "and", "thereby", "grant", "to", "public", "employee", "a", "broad", "constitutional", "employment", "right", "that", "private", "employee", "do", "not", "enjoy"]]}, {"text": "Two independent reasons, however, argue strongly for applying the public concern requirement to discipline claims brought both under the Free Speech and the Petition Clauses.", "start": 31.907, "stop": 41.834, "duration": 9.93, "cleanText": [["two", "independent", "reason", "however", "argue", "strongly", "for", "apply", "the", "public", "concern", "requirement", "to", "discipline", "claim", "bring", "both", "under", "the", "free", "speech", "and", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "First, the constitutional framework principles this Court has repeatedly identified in its public employment cases argue strongly for requiring it.", "start": 41.834, "stop": 51.592, "duration": 9.76, "cleanText": [["first", "the", "constitutional", "framework", "principle", "this", "court", "have", "repeatedly", "identify", "in", "its", "public", "employment", "case", "argue", "strongly", "for", "require", "it"]]}, {"text": "And second, McDonald v. Smith's principle of parity argues strongly for creating no hierarchy between the Free Speech and Petition Clauses.", "start": 51.592, "stop": 60.025, "duration": 8.43, "cleanText": [["and", "second", "mcdonald", "v", "smith", "s", "principle", "of", "parity", "argues", "strongly", "for", "create", "no", "hierarchy", "between", "the", "free", "speech", "and", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "When--", "start": 60.025, "stop": 60.696, "duration": 0.67, "cleanText": [["when"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "You agree that the Petition Clause is -- is different and does have a separate content?", "start": 60.696, "stop": 67.387, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["you", "agree", "that", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "be", "different", "and", "do", "have", "a", "separate", "content"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, we agree that the Petition Clause -- that when the Petition Clause and the Free Speech Clause cover the same activity, they apply -- they cover it under McDonald in the same way.", "start": 67.387, "stop": 82.359, "duration": 14.97, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "we", "agree", "that", "the", "petition", "clause", "that", "when", "the", "petition", "clause", "and", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "cover", "the", "same", "activity", "they", "apply", "they", "cover", "it", "under", "mcdonald", "in", "the", "same", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the Speech Clause, in the employment context, has been interpreted to cover the content.", "start": 82.359, "stop": 91.183, "duration": 8.82, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "speech", "clause", "in", "the", "employment", "context", "have", "be", "interpret", "to", "cover", "the", "content"]]}, {"text": "Whether it -- whether it applies or not depends upon the content, right?", "start": 91.183, "stop": 95.136, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["whether", "it", "whether", "it", "apply", "or", "not", "depend", "upon", "the", "content", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "One part of that inquiry turns on the content.", "start": 95.136, "stop": 98.341, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["one", "part", "of", "that", "inquiry", "turn", "on", "the", "content"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you want the Petition Clause also to turn on the content?", "start": 98.341, "stop": 103.37, "duration": 5.03, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "want", "the", "petition", "clause", "also", "to", "turn", "on", "the", "content"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Part of the inquiry, yes, Your Honor, should turn on the content.", "start": 103.37, "stop": 107.431, "duration": 4.06, "cleanText": [["part", "of", "the", "inquiry", "yes", "your", "honor", "should", "turn", "on", "the", "content"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But it seems to me you're either petitioning the government or you're not petitioning the government.", "start": 107.431, "stop": 112.507, "duration": 5.08, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "you", "be", "either", "petition", "the", "government", "or", "you", "be", "not", "petition", "the", "government"]]}, {"text": "Why -- why shouldn't the line be, if you're petitioning the government as employer is different from petitioning the government as ruler?", "start": 112.507, "stop": 128.022, "duration": 15.51, "cleanText": [["why", "why", "should", "not", "the", "line", "be", "if", "you", "be", "petition", "the", "government", "as", "employer", "be", "different", "from", "petition", "the", "government", "as", "ruler"]]}, {"text": "Why shouldn't that be the line that we draw?", "start": 128.022, "stop": 131.087, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["why", "should", "not", "that", "be", "the", "line", "that", "we", "draw"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the--", "start": 131.087, "stop": 132.004, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["well", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Which wouldn't necessarily break out the same way as whether it's a matter of private concern versus a matter of public concern.", "start": 132.004, "stop": 140.767, "duration": 8.76, "cleanText": [["which", "would", "not", "necessarily", "break", "out", "the", "same", "way", "as", "whether", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "private", "concern", "versus", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, this -- under the constitutional background principles this Court has developed, this Court should look at -- looks at how close to the core a particular example of employee activity is, and then talks about how much of a burden that kind of activity poses to the efficient operation of the workplace.", "start": 140.767, "stop": 163.88, "duration": 23.11, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "this", "under", "the", "constitutional", "background", "principle", "this", "court", "have", "develop", "this", "court", "should", "look", "at", "look", "at", "how", "close", "to", "the", "core", "a", "particular", "example", "of", "employee", "activity", "be", "and", "then", "talk", "about", "how", "much", "of", "a", "burden", "that", "kind", "of", "activity", "pose", "to", "the", "efficient", "operation", "of", "the", "workplace"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the core -- the core of the Petition Clause is petitioning.", "start": 163.88, "stop": 168.936, "duration": 5.06, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "core", "the", "core", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "petition"]]}, {"text": "The core of the Free Speech Clause is political speech, of course -- speech in public interest -- but the core of the Petition Clause is quite different.", "start": 168.936, "stop": 181.123, "duration": 12.19, "cleanText": [["the", "core", "of", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "be", "political", "speech", "of", "course", "speech", "in", "public", "interest", "but", "the", "core", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "quite", "different"]]}, {"text": "It's simply whether you're petitioning.", "start": 181.123, "stop": 183.362, "duration": 2.24, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "simply", "whether", "you", "be", "petition"]]}, {"text": "Surely you -- you could petition the -- most of the petitions in the early years were regarding private matters; isn't that right?", "start": 183.362, "stop": 192.654, "duration": 9.29, "cleanText": [["surely", "you", "you", "could", "petition", "the", "most", "of", "the", "petition", "in", "the", "early", "year", "we", "be", "regard", "private", "matter", "be", "not", "that", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is right, Your Honor, just as most examples of speech concern private matters, too.", "start": 192.654, "stop": 197.464, "duration": 4.81, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "your", "honor", "just", "as", "most", "example", "of", "speech", "concern", "private", "matter", "too"]]}, {"text": "Yet that does not define the core of the Free Speech Clause.", "start": 197.464, "stop": 199.798, "duration": 2.33, "cleanText": [["yet", "that", "do", "not", "define", "the", "core", "of", "the", "free", "speech", "clause"]]}, {"text": "There's not an empirical inquiry.", "start": 199.798, "stop": 201.897, "duration": 2.1, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "not", "an", "empirical", "inquiry"]]}, {"text": "That depends upon the purpose of the clause.", "start": 201.897, "stop": 204.248, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["that", "depend", "upon", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "clause"]]}, {"text": "And as this Court stated very definitely in McDonald, the core of the Petition Clause, like the Free Speech Clause, was -- was aimed at promoting democratic self-government.", "start": 204.248, "stop": 216.759, "duration": 12.51, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "this", "court", "state", "very", "definitely", "in", "mcdonald", "the", "core", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "like", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "be", "be", "aim", "at", "promote", "democratic", "self", "government"]]}, {"text": "Petitioning is a particular form of speech.", "start": 216.759, "stop": 220.011, "duration": 3.25, "cleanText": [["petitioning", "be", "a", "particular", "form", "of", "speech"]]}, {"text": "It is speech directed to a particular audience, the government, some arm of government, some individual in government, and it is speech that has a particular purpose: Asking for a change of some sort in government policy.", "start": 220.011, "stop": 231.778, "duration": 11.77, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "speech", "direct", "to", "a", "particular", "audience", "the", "government", "some", "arm", "of", "government", "some", "individual", "in", "government", "and", "it", "be", "speech", "that", "have", "a", "particular", "purpose", "ask", "for", "a", "change", "of", "some", "sort", "in", "government", "policy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's true, and it seems to me the -- the core is involved whenever you're asking for a change.", "start": 231.778, "stop": 238.967, "duration": 7.19, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "true", "and", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "the", "the", "core", "be", "involve", "whenever", "you", "be", "ask", "for", "a", "change"]]}, {"text": "And it seems to me that the key distinction, if there is one, is whether you're asking for a change in -- by your employer in your employment conditions or a change by the government in some matters over which the government has control as -- as sovereign.", "start": 238.967, "stop": 259.245, "duration": 20.28, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "the", "key", "distinction", "if", "there", "be", "one", "be", "whether", "you", "be", "ask", "for", "a", "change", "in", "by", "your", "employer", "in", "your", "employment", "condition", "or", "a", "change", "by", "the", "government", "in", "some", "matter", "over", "which", "the", "government", "have", "control", "as", "as", "sovereign"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Your Honor, in practice, that inquiry would not align much differently than the Connick inquiry.", "start": 259.245, "stop": 267.277, "duration": 8.03, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "honor", "in", "practice", "that", "inquiry", "would", "not", "align", "much", "differently", "than", "the", "connick", "inquiry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "It may well be, may well be.", "start": 267.277, "stop": 269.766, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["it", "may", "well", "be", "may", "well", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "And in this particular case, designing a kind of threshold inquiry along those lines would actually advantage Petitioners.", "start": 269.766, "stop": 281.188, "duration": 11.42, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "this", "particular", "case", "design", "a", "kind", "of", "threshold", "inquiry", "along", "those", "line", "would", "actually", "advantage", "petitioner"]]}, {"text": "One difficulty in application, though, is that this Court has always identified the purpose of the Connick threshold test as categoricalizing in a way the Pickering balancing inquiry.", "start": 281.188, "stop": 294.385, "duration": 13.2, "cleanText": [["one", "difficulty", "in", "application", "though", "be", "that", "this", "court", "have", "always", "identify", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "connick", "threshold", "test", "as", "categoricalizing", "in", "a", "way", "the", "pickering", "balancing", "inquiry"]]}, {"text": "And if you had a threshold test that basically did not match, was a little oblique to the Pickering balancing inquiry, it would create much more work for the lower courts along the way.", "start": 294.385, "stop": 307.026, "duration": 12.64, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "you", "have", "a", "threshold", "test", "that", "basically", "do", "not", "match", "be", "a", "little", "oblique", "to", "the", "pickering", "balancing", "inquiry", "it", "would", "create", "much", "more", "work", "for", "the", "low", "court", "along", "the", "way"]]}, {"text": "Or perhaps this Court would want to change the Pickering balancing inquiry.", "start": 307.026, "stop": 310.992, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["or", "perhaps", "this", "court", "would", "want", "to", "change", "the", "pickering", "balance", "inquiry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would they have to do both?", "start": 310.992, "stop": 312.002, "duration": 1.01, "cleanText": [["would", "they", "have", "to", "do", "both"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "They might well, Your Honor.", "start": 312.002, "stop": 313.063, "duration": 1.06, "cleanText": [["they", "might", "well", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "If the Pickering balancing inquiry still aligns with the traditional framework that this Court has described in its employment cases, what I describe, and this other inquiry, which you're suggesting, Justice Scalia, was somewhat oblique to it, then it might conceivably be necessary to do both.", "start": 313.063, "stop": 330.915, "duration": 17.85, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "pickering", "balancing", "inquiry", "still", "align", "with", "the", "traditional", "framework", "that", "this", "court", "have", "describe", "in", "its", "employment", "case", "what", "i", "describe", "and", "this", "other", "inquiry", "which", "you", "be", "suggest", "justice", "scalia", "be", "somewhat", "oblique", "to", "it", "then", "it", "might", "conceivably", "be", "necessary", "to", "do", "both"]]}, {"text": "One--", "start": 330.915, "stop": 331.208, "duration": 0.29, "cleanText": [["one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you're proceeding with a claim under two separate provisions of the Constitution, it should not be surprising that you might have two different tests.", "start": 331.208, "stop": 341.108, "duration": 9.9, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "be", "proceed", "with", "a", "claim", "under", "two", "separate", "provision", "of", "the", "constitution", "it", "should", "not", "be", "surprise", "that", "you", "might", "have", "two", "different", "test"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, Your Honor, then that might argue for more reengineering of the rest of the -- the enterprise as well, a step that this Court has not identified as appropriate under--", "start": 341.108, "stop": 353.541, "duration": 12.43, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "honor", "then", "that", "might", "argue", "for", "more", "reengineering", "of", "the", "rest", "of", "the", "the", "enterprise", "as", "well", "a", "step", "that", "this", "court", "have", "not", "identify", "as", "appropriate", "under"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why would it make -- why would it make a difference at what you call the balancing stage whether it is -- whether the distinction is between public speech and private speech on the one hand or government as employer and government as sovereign on the other?", "start": 353.541, "stop": 374.462, "duration": 20.92, "cleanText": [["why", "would", "it", "make", "why", "would", "it", "make", "a", "difference", "at", "what", "you", "call", "the", "balancing", "stage", "whether", "it", "be", "whether", "the", "distinction", "be", "between", "public", "speech", "and", "private", "speech", "on", "the", "one", "hand", "or", "government", "as", "employer", "and", "government", "as", "sovereign", "on", "the", "other"]]}, {"text": "Why would there be any difference?", "start": 374.462, "stop": 377.298, "duration": 2.84, "cleanText": [["why", "would", "there", "be", "any", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, Your Honor, if at the first stage the Court is running an inquiry that is something different from Connick, that is not going to map onto traditional Pickering balancing, at least as this Court has described it, at the second stage.", "start": 377.298, "stop": 392.283, "duration": 14.99, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "honor", "if", "at", "the", "first", "stage", "the", "court", "be", "run", "an", "inquiry", "that", "be", "something", "different", "from", "connick", "that", "be", "not", "go", "to", "map", "onto", "traditional", "pickering", "balancing", "at", "least", "as", "this", "court", "have", "describe", "it", "at", "the", "second", "stage"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why not?", "start": 392.283, "stop": 392.704, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["why", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because, Your Honor, Pickering balancing has gone to things like how -- how -- how important that particular example of speech is, how close it is to the core of what the First Amendment protects, and then that is weighed against the kind of burden it would place on the government to have that activity protected in a very strong way.", "start": 392.704, "stop": 420.623, "duration": 27.92, "cleanText": [["because", "your", "honor", "pickering", "balancing", "have", "go", "to", "thing", "like", "how", "how", "how", "important", "that", "particular", "example", "of", "speech", "be", "how", "close", "it", "be", "to", "the", "core", "of", "what", "the", "first", "amendment", "protects", "and", "then", "that", "be", "weigh", "against", "the", "kind", "of", "burden", "it", "would", "place", "on", "the", "government", "to", "have", "that", "activity", "protect", "in", "a", "very", "strong", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think all you're saying is that one of the elements of Pickering balancing is the element of Petition Clause jurisprudence, as I suggested it -- it might be applied; that is, in Pickering balancing, certainly you have to ask, was what the individual was asking for a change in employment conditions?", "start": 420.623, "stop": 446.3, "duration": 25.68, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "all", "you", "be", "say", "be", "that", "one", "of", "the", "element", "of", "pickering", "balancing", "be", "the", "element", "of", "petition", "clause", "jurisprudence", "as", "i", "suggest", "it", "it", "might", "be", "apply", "that", "be", "in", "pickering", "balancing", "certainly", "you", "have", "to", "ask", "be", "what", "the", "individual", "be", "ask", "for", "a", "change", "in", "employment", "condition"]]}, {"text": "That would be one of the questions.", "start": 446.3, "stop": 448.185, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "one", "of", "the", "question"]]}, {"text": "If so, it was a private matter, and then you go on to the rest of the balancing.", "start": 448.185, "stop": 451.313, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["if", "so", "it", "be", "a", "private", "matter", "and", "then", "you", "go", "on", "to", "the", "rest", "of", "the", "balancing"]]}, {"text": "But it seems to me you have to make that determination under Pickering balancing anyway, and once you make it, you've answered the -- the Petition Clause question.", "start": 451.313, "stop": 462.005, "duration": 10.69, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "you", "have", "to", "make", "that", "determination", "under", "pickering", "balance", "anyway", "and", "once", "you", "make", "it", "you", "have", "answer", "the", "the", "petition", "clause", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Your Honor, if this -- if this Court were to proceed down that road, Petitioners, I believe, would still end up victorious.", "start": 462.005, "stop": 472.975, "duration": 10.97, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "honor", "if", "this", "if", "this", "court", "we", "be", "to", "proceed", "down", "that", "road", "petitioner", "i", "believe", "would", "still", "end", "up", "victorious"]]}, {"text": "This is a case, as I understand your -- your approach, where the petition does concern purely employment matters.", "start": 472.975, "stop": 482.814, "duration": 9.84, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "a", "case", "as", "i", "understand", "your", "your", "approach", "where", "the", "petition", "do", "concern", "purely", "employment", "matter"]]}, {"text": "It is not a petition aimed at or directed at the government in its capacity as sovereign, so under that kind of analysis, that is where the initial trigger, this case, would have not been constitutionalized.", "start": 482.814, "stop": 497.923, "duration": 15.11, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "petition", "aim", "at", "or", "direct", "at", "the", "government", "in", "its", "capacity", "as", "sovereign", "so", "under", "that", "kind", "of", "analysis", "that", "be", "where", "the", "initial", "trigger", "this", "case", "would", "have", "not", "be", "constitutionalize"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "What kind of case, hypothetically, would qualify under your theory as a petitioning case to the sovereign?", "start": 497.923, "stop": 507.542, "duration": 9.62, "cleanText": [["what", "kind", "of", "case", "hypothetically", "would", "qualify", "under", "your", "theory", "as", "a", "petitioning", "case", "to", "the", "sovereign"]]}, {"text": "Would a claim of retaliation because of a termination based on race qualify?", "start": 507.542, "stop": 513.176, "duration": 5.63, "cleanText": [["would", "a", "claim", "of", "retaliation", "because", "of", "a", "termination", "base", "on", "race", "qualify"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "It would depend upon the particular claims involved, or statements in the petition.", "start": 513.176, "stop": 521.906, "duration": 8.73, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "depend", "upon", "the", "particular", "claim", "involve", "or", "statement", "in", "the", "petition"]]}, {"text": "If it were a statement that there was a policy, involved a petition against a policy in a government department involving race, that would certainly qualify.", "start": 521.906, "stop": 530.993, "duration": 9.09, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "we", "be", "a", "statement", "that", "there", "be", "a", "policy", "involve", "a", "petition", "against", "a", "policy", "in", "a", "government", "department", "involve", "race", "that", "would", "certainly", "qualify"]]}, {"text": "That would be like the Gibbons case under the Free Speech Clause, Your Honor.", "start": 530.993, "stop": 534.557, "duration": 3.56, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "like", "the", "gibbon", "case", "under", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "If, however, it were a one-off allegation that a particular, say, low-level governmental supervisor had engaged in a form of discriminatory activity--", "start": 534.557, "stop": 547.088, "duration": 12.53, "cleanText": [["if", "however", "it", "we", "be", "a", "one", "off", "allegation", "that", "a", "particular", "say", "low", "level", "governmental", "supervisor", "have", "engage", "in", "a", "form", "of", "discriminatory", "activity"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Doesn't that get to the -- to the merits of the case?", "start": 547.088, "stop": 549.671, "duration": 2.58, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "that", "get", "to", "the", "to", "the", "merit", "of", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "You have to from -- you can't invite a question as to whether the sovereign is responsible until you litigate the issue.", "start": 549.671, "stop": 558.729, "duration": 9.06, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "to", "from", "you", "can", "not", "invite", "a", "question", "as", "to", "whether", "the", "sovereign", "be", "responsible", "until", "you", "litigate", "the", "issue"]]}, {"text": "So what is the -- addressing Justice Scalia's question to you, what would qualify as a petition to the employer as opposed to a petition to the sovereign and why?", "start": 558.729, "stop": 575.145, "duration": 16.42, "cleanText": [["so", "what", "be", "the", "address", "justice", "scalia", "s", "question", "to", "you", "what", "would", "qualify", "as", "a", "petition", "to", "the", "employer", "as", "oppose", "to", "a", "petition", "to", "the", "sovereign", "and", "why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, a petition to the employer about changing the hours of employment--", "start": 575.145, "stop": 583.084, "duration": 7.94, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "a", "petition", "to", "the", "employer", "about", "change", "the", "hour", "of", "employment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Those are clear cases.", "start": 583.084, "stop": 584.005, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["those", "be", "clear", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--for overtime--", "start": 584.005, "stop": 584.551, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["for", "overtime"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "I was asking the flip.", "start": 584.551, "stop": 586.463, "duration": 1.91, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "ask", "the", "flip"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The flip.", "start": 586.463, "stop": 587.149, "duration": 0.69, "cleanText": [["the", "flip"]]}, {"text": "A petition, a complaint to an employer about the employer's pervasive or apparently pervasive policies in violation of the law, would certainly qualify as something to -- a petition to the sovereign.", "start": 587.149, "stop": 606.588, "duration": 19.44, "cleanText": [["a", "petition", "a", "complaint", "to", "an", "employer", "about", "the", "employer", "s", "pervasive", "or", "apparently", "pervasive", "policy", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "law", "would", "certainly", "qualify", "as", "something", "to", "a", "petition", "to", "the", "sovereign"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course, you have to wrestle with the same problem if you apply the other test that you -- you were proposing.", "start": 606.588, "stop": 613.59, "duration": 7, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "you", "have", "to", "wrestle", "with", "the", "same", "problem", "if", "you", "apply", "the", "other", "test", "that", "you", "you", "we", "be", "propose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "For sure.", "start": 613.59, "stop": 614.288, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["for", "sure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Namely, whether it's a private matter or a matter of public concern.", "start": 614.288, "stop": 618.26, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["namely", "whether", "it", "be", "a", "private", "matter", "or", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}, {"text": "You confront the same difficulty, don't you?", "start": 618.26, "stop": 620.546, "duration": 2.29, "cleanText": [["you", "confront", "the", "same", "difficulty", "do", "not", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "You certainly do, Your Honor, and presumably this Court would look at some of the same factors involved there: The form, the content, and the context of the communication.", "start": 620.546, "stop": 629.869, "duration": 9.32, "cleanText": [["you", "certainly", "do", "your", "honor", "and", "presumably", "this", "court", "would", "look", "at", "some", "of", "the", "same", "factor", "involve", "there", "the", "form", "the", "content", "and", "the", "context", "of", "the", "communication"]]}, {"text": "All of those things are relevant.", "start": 629.869, "stop": 631.207, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["all", "of", "those", "thing", "be", "relevant"]]}, {"text": "This Court has admitted that that inquiry is sometimes messy, that there are some -- many cases where the line of distinction is not clear.", "start": 631.207, "stop": 639.594, "duration": 8.39, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "have", "admit", "that", "that", "inquiry", "be", "sometimes", "messy", "that", "there", "be", "some", "many", "case", "where", "the", "line", "of", "distinction", "be", "not", "clear"]]}, {"text": "But it is -- this Court has not hesitated to apply that test because of its importance to the public employment environment.", "start": 639.594, "stop": 647.873, "duration": 8.28, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "be", "this", "court", "have", "not", "hesitate", "to", "apply", "that", "test", "because", "of", "its", "importance", "to", "the", "public", "employment", "environment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Ortiz, you're not drawing any line depending on the branch of government, in other words, executive, legislature.", "start": 647.873, "stop": 660.806, "duration": 12.93, "cleanText": [["mr", "ortiz", "you", "be", "not", "draw", "any", "line", "depend", "on", "the", "branch", "of", "government", "in", "other", "word", "executive", "legislature"]]}, {"text": "Those are certainly branches of government to which one can petition.", "start": 660.806, "stop": 666.24, "duration": 5.43, "cleanText": [["those", "be", "certainly", "branch", "of", "government", "to", "which", "one", "can", "petition"]]}, {"text": "But access to court you agree comes within the Petition Clause?", "start": 666.24, "stop": 672.93, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["but", "access", "to", "court", "you", "agree", "come", "within", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "A lawsuit, pursuing a lawsuit, is definitely a form of petitioning activity, Your Honor.", "start": 672.93, "stop": 679.469, "duration": 6.54, "cleanText": [["a", "lawsuit", "pursue", "a", "lawsuit", "be", "definitely", "a", "form", "of", "petition", "activity", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Petitioners do not contest that.", "start": 679.469, "stop": 681.583, "duration": 2.11, "cleanText": [["petitioner", "do", "not", "contest", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "What about the -- this as I understand it, came up originally as arbitration under the -- wasn't it under the collective bargaining contract?", "start": 681.583, "stop": 693.879, "duration": 12.3, "cleanText": [["what", "about", "the", "this", "as", "i", "understand", "it", "come", "up", "originally", "as", "arbitration", "under", "the", "be", "not", "it", "under", "the", "collective", "bargaining", "contract"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, that is the case.", "start": 693.879, "stop": 695.467, "duration": 1.59, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "that", "be", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would that count also, because it is a mechanism set up by a government employer?", "start": 695.467, "stop": 700.369, "duration": 4.9, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "count", "also", "because", "it", "be", "a", "mechanism", "set", "up", "by", "a", "government", "employer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "It would qualify under the original conception of what a petition is all about that was in this case.", "start": 700.369, "stop": 706.39, "duration": 6.02, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "qualify", "under", "the", "original", "conception", "of", "what", "a", "petition", "be", "all", "about", "that", "be", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "It is Petitioner's view that it would not qualify under the access to courts definition or conception of petition that Respondent has developed since the case was first before the district court.", "start": 706.39, "stop": 719.154, "duration": 12.76, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "petitioner", "s", "view", "that", "it", "would", "not", "qualify", "under", "the", "access", "to", "court", "definition", "or", "conception", "of", "petition", "that", "respondent", "have", "develop", "since", "the", "case", "be", "first", "before", "the", "district", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "If -- if lawsuits are covered by the Petition Clause, why is it that in the innumerable cases this Court has had concerning what due process of law consists of, we've never mentioned what the Petition Clause requires.", "start": 719.154, "stop": 739.881, "duration": 20.73, "cleanText": [["if", "if", "lawsuit", "be", "cover", "by", "the", "petition", "clause", "why", "be", "it", "that", "in", "the", "innumerable", "case", "this", "court", "have", "have", "concern", "what", "due", "process", "of", "law", "consists", "of", "we", "have", "never", "mention", "what", "the", "petition", "clause", "require"]]}, {"text": "I mean, if the Petition Clause guarantees access to the courts, certainly there are some minimum requirements that it imposes as well, and I don't recall any of our cases dealing with lawsuits that mention the Petition Clause.", "start": 739.881, "stop": 753.453, "duration": 13.57, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "if", "the", "petition", "clause", "guarantee", "access", "to", "the", "court", "certainly", "there", "be", "some", "minimum", "requirement", "that", "it", "impose", "as", "well", "and", "i", "do", "not", "recall", "any", "of", "our", "case", "deal", "with", "lawsuit", "that", "mention", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "That's rather extraordinary if indeed it governs all lawsuits.", "start": 753.453, "stop": 756.082, "duration": 2.63, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "rather", "extraordinary", "if", "indeed", "it", "govern", "all", "lawsuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Your Honor, that might be explained by the fact that the Due Process Clause has been interpreted more robustly and supplies a certain floor of constitutional protection for lawsuits.", "start": 756.082, "stop": 767.66, "duration": 11.58, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "honor", "that", "might", "be", "explain", "by", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "due", "process", "clause", "have", "be", "interpret", "more", "robustly", "and", "supply", "a", "certain", "floor", "of", "constitutional", "protection", "for", "lawsuit"]]}, {"text": "And the Petition Clause, since it is directed at petitions generally and in particular the framers, the evidence is, had in mind not petitions to the courts, but petitions to the legislature, if lawsuits--", "start": 767.66, "stop": 784.361, "duration": 16.7, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "petition", "clause", "since", "it", "be", "direct", "at", "petition", "generally", "and", "in", "particular", "the", "framer", "the", "evidence", "be", "have", "in", "mind", "not", "petition", "to", "the", "court", "but", "petition", "to", "the", "legislature", "if", "lawsuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Maybe that's all they had in mind, or petitions to the executive as well.", "start": 784.361, "stop": 789.047, "duration": 4.69, "cleanText": [["maybe", "that", "be", "all", "they", "have", "in", "mind", "or", "petition", "to", "the", "executive", "as", "well"]]}, {"text": "What -- what evidence do you have that it applied to lawsuits?", "start": 789.047, "stop": 794.586, "duration": 5.54, "cleanText": [["what", "what", "evidence", "do", "you", "have", "that", "it", "apply", "to", "lawsuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The evidence is that developed by Professor Andrews, and the argument is a somewhat slender one that goes as follows: At the time of founding, Congress was the central sort of clearinghouse for petitions and handled both what we think of as the stereotypical paradigmatic petitions, pleas to Congress to sort of change the law, and also handled a lot of private bills.", "start": 794.586, "stop": 825.478, "duration": 30.89, "cleanText": [["the", "evidence", "be", "that", "develop", "by", "professor", "andrew", "and", "the", "argument", "be", "a", "somewhat", "slender", "one", "that", "go", "as", "follow", "at", "the", "time", "of", "founding", "congress", "be", "the", "central", "sort", "of", "clearinghouse", "for", "petition", "and", "handle", "both", "what", "we", "think", "of", "as", "the", "stereotypical", "paradigmatic", "petition", "plea", "to", "congress", "to", "sort", "of", "change", "the", "law", "and", "also", "handle", "a", "lot", "of", "private", "bill"]]}, {"text": "Over time, Congress handed over much of the responsibility for handling the things that came through private bills to the courts, and so to the extent -- this is Respondent's argument -- that the courts handled, took over those things, the lawsuits are protected.", "start": 825.478, "stop": 843.532, "duration": 18.05, "cleanText": [["over", "time", "congress", "hand", "over", "much", "of", "the", "responsibility", "for", "handle", "the", "thing", "that", "come", "through", "private", "bill", "to", "the", "court", "and", "so", "to", "the", "extent", "this", "be", "respondent", "s", "argument", "that", "the", "court", "handle", "take", "over", "those", "thing", "the", "lawsuit", "be", "protect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "I agree with you that that's slender.", "start": 843.532, "stop": 845.241, "duration": 1.71, "cleanText": [["i", "agree", "with", "you", "that", "that", "be", "slender"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Your Honor.", "start": 845.241, "stop": 848.104, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you are not challenging that, as I understand.", "start": 848.104, "stop": 852.2, "duration": 4.1, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "be", "not", "challenge", "that", "as", "i", "understand"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor.", "start": 852.2, "stop": 853.757, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "In the district court it was conceded that the grievance activity would be -- was protected.", "start": 853.757, "stop": 862.035, "duration": 8.28, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "district", "court", "it", "be", "concede", "that", "the", "grievance", "activity", "would", "be", "be", "protect"]]}, {"text": "However, Petitioners do contest quite sharply that under Respondent's new view of the Petition Clause that the things of central importance are lawsuits and other communications that would be protected, perhaps be protected, otherwise under the access to courts doctrine, that arbitration, the arbitration involved in this case, does not count and should not receive any kind of heightened protection.", "start": 862.035, "stop": 889.55, "duration": 27.51, "cleanText": [["however", "petitioner", "do", "contest", "quite", "sharply", "that", "under", "respondent", "s", "new", "view", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "that", "the", "thing", "of", "central", "importance", "be", "lawsuit", "and", "other", "communication", "that", "would", "be", "protect", "perhaps", "be", "protect", "otherwise", "under", "the", "access", "to", "court", "doctrine", "that", "arbitration", "the", "arbitration", "involve", "in", "this", "case", "do", "not", "count", "and", "should", "not", "receive", "any", "kind", "of", "heighten", "protection"]]}, {"text": "The problem, much of the problem here, is the theory of what is a petition from Respondent's side has changed from the district court to this Court.", "start": 889.55, "stop": 898.233, "duration": 8.68, "cleanText": [["the", "problem", "much", "of", "the", "problem", "here", "be", "the", "theory", "of", "what", "be", "a", "petition", "from", "respondent", "s", "side", "have", "change", "from", "the", "district", "court", "to", "this", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Ortiz, can I try a hypothetical on you?", "start": 898.233, "stop": 900.304, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["mr", "ortiz", "can", "i", "try", "a", "hypothetical", "on", "you"]]}, {"text": "Suppose that there is a city employee and unrelated to the fact that he is a city employee the government takes some part of his property without just compensation.", "start": 900.304, "stop": 911.929, "duration": 11.63, "cleanText": [["suppose", "that", "there", "be", "a", "city", "employee", "and", "unrelated", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "he", "be", "a", "city", "employee", "the", "government", "take", "some", "part", "of", "his", "property", "without", "just", "compensation"]]}, {"text": "And he sues the government, and the government says, somebody says, his employer, that his supervisor said: Do you know what he's just done?", "start": 911.929, "stop": 920.941, "duration": 9.01, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "sue", "the", "government", "and", "the", "government", "say", "somebody", "say", "his", "employer", "that", "his", "supervisor", "say", "do", "you", "know", "what", "he", "be", "just", "do"]]}, {"text": "He's just sued the city; I think we should fire him.", "start": 920.941, "stop": 923.43, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "just", "sue", "the", "city", "i", "think", "we", "should", "fire", "him"]]}, {"text": "And he brings a retaliation claim.", "start": 923.43, "stop": 927.132, "duration": 3.7, "cleanText": [["and", "he", "bring", "a", "retaliation", "claim"]]}, {"text": "Is that protected under the Petition Clause?", "start": 927.132, "stop": 929.125, "duration": 1.99, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "protect", "under", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, it would be protected for two different reasons.", "start": 929.125, "stop": 932.098, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "it", "would", "be", "protect", "for", "two", "different", "reason"]]}, {"text": "First, that would -- similar activity would be protected under the Free Speech Clause, so that would preserve the principle of parity.", "start": 932.098, "stop": 937.841, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["first", "that", "would", "similar", "activity", "would", "be", "protect", "under", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "so", "that", "would", "preserve", "the", "principle", "of", "parity"]]}, {"text": "Second--", "start": 937.841, "stop": 939.147, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["second"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Really?", "start": 939.147, "stop": 939.599, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["really"]]}, {"text": "What has he done that's protected under the Free Speech Clause?", "start": 939.599, "stop": 941.824, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["what", "have", "he", "do", "that", "be", "protect", "under", "the", "free", "speech", "clause"]]}, {"text": "He has brought a suit saying: I'm entitled to just compensation.", "start": 941.824, "stop": 945.217, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["he", "have", "bring", "a", "suit", "say", "I", "be", "entitle", "to", "just", "compensation"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me -- the reason I ask is because this seems to me a purely private matter which would not get protection under your test.", "start": 945.217, "stop": 954.759, "duration": 9.54, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "the", "reason", "i", "ask", "be", "because", "this", "seem", "to", "me", "a", "purely", "private", "matter", "which", "would", "not", "get", "protection", "under", "your", "test"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It's not employment-related or related to his particular job, and this Court has always drawn the distinction there.", "start": 954.759, "stop": 961.559, "duration": 6.8, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "not", "employment", "relate", "or", "relate", "to", "his", "particular", "job", "and", "this", "court", "have", "always", "draw", "the", "distinction", "there"]]}, {"text": "For example, in National Treasury Employees Union this Court applied that kind of analysis.", "start": 961.559, "stop": 966.182, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["for", "example", "in", "national", "treasury", "employee", "union", "this", "court", "apply", "that", "kind", "of", "analysis"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see, so that goes back to Justice Scalia's difference test, which is it's not a matter of public concern versus private concern, but it's a matter of employment-related versus not employment-related, correct?", "start": 966.182, "stop": 976.519, "duration": 10.34, "cleanText": [["i", "see", "so", "that", "go", "back", "to", "justice", "scalia", "s", "difference", "test", "which", "be", "it", "be", "not", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "versus", "private", "concern", "but", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "employment", "relate", "versus", "not", "employment", "relate", "correct"]]}, {"text": "Is that correct?", "start": 976.519, "stop": 976.641, "duration": 0.12, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel R. Ortiz", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that shows how closely those two things have been related in this Court's approach.", "start": 976.641, "stop": 982.106, "duration": 5.47, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "show", "how", "closely", "those", "two", "thing", "have", "be", "relate", "in", "this", "court", "s", "approach"]]}, {"text": "In -- but certainly something that is privately-related, a public employee is complaining about tax assessment or something like that and tries to sue for retaliation under, under that theory, not for anything related to his or her job, this Court -- under this Court's and the lower court's application of the Connick principles, there would be no problem there treating it as speech or as a petition.", "start": 982.106, "stop": 1011.536, "duration": 29.43, "cleanText": [["in", "but", "certainly", "something", "that", "be", "privately", "relate", "a", "public", "employee", "be", "complain", "about", "tax", "assessment", "or", "something", "like", "that", "and", "try", "to", "sue", "for", "retaliation", "under", "under", "that", "theory", "not", "for", "anything", "relate", "to", "his", "or", "her", "job", "this", "court", "under", "this", "court", "s", "and", "the", "low", "court", "s", "application", "of", "the", "connick", "principle", "there", "would", "be", "no", "problem", "there", "treat", "it", "as", "speech", "or", "as", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "So it is only when the lawsuit or the petition involves something related to the person's employment that these particular -- this particular test would kick in.", "start": 1011.536, "stop": 1025.276, "duration": 13.74, "cleanText": [["so", "it", "be", "only", "when", "the", "lawsuit", "or", "the", "petition", "involve", "something", "relate", "to", "the", "person", "s", "employment", "that", "these", "particular", "this", "particular", "test", "would", "kick", "in"]]}, {"text": "And that's consistent, Your Honor, with this Court's twin background constitutional framework principles, one that you look at how much disruption something is likely to pose to the workforce and how central it is to the particular constitutional provision involved.", "start": 1025.276, "stop": 1042.892, "duration": 17.62, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "consistent", "your", "honor", "with", "this", "court", "s", "twin", "background", "constitutional", "framework", "principle", "one", "that", "you", "look", "at", "how", "much", "disruption", "something", "be", "likely", "to", "pose", "to", "the", "workforce", "and", "how", "central", "it", "be", "to", "the", "particular", "constitutional", "provision", "involve"]]}, {"text": "In this case, if in general it's not employment-related the government has much less interest in worrying over it this way and applying the Connick threshold test is much less justified.", "start": 1042.892, "stop": 1054.751, "duration": 11.86, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "if", "in", "general", "it", "be", "not", "employment", "relate", "the", "government", "have", "much", "less", "interest", "in", "worry", "over", "it", "this", "way", "and", "apply", "the", "connick", "threshold", "test", "be", "much", "less", "justified"]]}, {"text": "You would have to do Pickering balancing, proceed directly to Pickering balancing in that case.", "start": 1054.751, "stop": 1059.917, "duration": 5.17, "cleanText": [["you", "would", "have", "to", "do", "pickering", "balancing", "proceed", "directly", "to", "pickering", "balance", "in", "that", "case"]]}, {"text": "Now, Your Honor, Respondent's view presents several problems of sort of practical application, or would, to this Court.", "start": 1059.917, "stop": 1072.293, "duration": 12.38, "cleanText": [["now", "your", "honor", "respondent", "s", "view", "present", "several", "problem", "of", "sort", "of", "practical", "application", "or", "would", "to", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "First, it would allow for the easy circumvention of Connick, which is a test that on the free speech side this Court has long held is very important for the public employment field to work efficiently.", "start": 1072.293, "stop": 1087.514, "duration": 15.22, "cleanText": [["first", "it", "would", "allow", "for", "the", "easy", "circumvention", "of", "connick", "which", "be", "a", "test", "that", "on", "the", "free", "speech", "side", "this", "court", "have", "long", "hold", "be", "very", "important", "for", "the", "public", "employment", "field", "to", "work", "efficiently"]]}, {"text": "It would be very easy for a particular employee to take activity that Connick would not allow to proceed, to turn into a lawsuit on the free speech clause, and just by rephrasing it, respinning it, whatever, to turn it into a petition where under Respondent's rule the result would be very different.", "start": 1087.514, "stop": 1106.455, "duration": 18.94, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "be", "very", "easy", "for", "a", "particular", "employee", "to", "take", "activity", "that", "connick", "would", "not", "allow", "to", "proceed", "to", "turn", "into", "a", "lawsuit", "on", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "and", "just", "by", "rephrase", "it", "respinning", "it", "whatever", "to", "turn", "it", "into", "a", "petition", "where", "under", "respondent", "s", "rule", "the", "result", "would", "be", "very", "different"]]}, {"text": "It also would require the Court to create a hierarchy between speech claims and petition claims, and, more importantly, if the Court were to go down the particular road that Respondent describes and see the center of the Petition Clause as defined by the access to courts doctrine it would create a hierarchy among different forms of petition.", "start": 1106.455, "stop": 1127.45, "duration": 21, "cleanText": [["it", "also", "would", "require", "the", "court", "to", "create", "a", "hierarchy", "between", "speech", "claim", "and", "petition", "claim", "and", "more", "importantly", "if", "the", "court", "we", "be", "to", "go", "down", "the", "particular", "road", "that", "respondent", "describes", "and", "see", "the", "center", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "as", "define", "by", "the", "access", "to", "court", "doctrine", "it", "would", "create", "a", "hierarchy", "among", "different", "form", "of", "petition"]]}, {"text": "All of a sudden, petitions that at the founding were thought to be at the periphery, if there, of the Petition Clause would define its center, and a paradigmatic petition of a letter to Congress asking it to change its position on something would not be covered at all.", "start": 1127.45, "stop": 1145.597, "duration": 18.15, "cleanText": [["all", "of", "a", "sudden", "petition", "that", "at", "the", "founding", "we", "be", "think", "to", "be", "at", "the", "periphery", "if", "there", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "would", "define", "its", "center", "and", "a", "paradigmatic", "petition", "of", "a", "letter", "to", "congress", "ask", "it", "to", "change", "its", "position", "on", "something", "would", "not", "be", "cover", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "If there are no further questions, I would like to retain my remaining time for rebuttal.", "start": 1145.597, "stop": 1151.106, "duration": 5.51, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "no", "further", "question", "i", "would", "like", "to", "retain", "my", "remain", "time", "for", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Ortiz.", "start": 1151.106, "stop": 1152.07, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "ortiz"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Palmore.", "start": 1152.07, "stop": 1160.195, "duration": 8.13, "cleanText": [["mr", "palmore"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 1160.195, "stop": 1163.059, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "The Third Circuit rule here at issue is flawed for two fundamental reasons.", "start": 1163.059, "stop": 1166.421, "duration": 3.36, "cleanText": [["the", "third", "circuit", "rule", "here", "at", "issue", "be", "flaw", "for", "two", "fundamental", "reason"]]}, {"text": "First, contrary to this Court's admonitions, it quite literally constitutionalizes the employee grievance process by supplanting carefully calibrated nonconstitutional safeguards and by providing a potential First Amendment claim in Federal court to any employee who has filed a grievance on a matter of only private interest.", "start": 1166.421, "stop": 1183.259, "duration": 16.84, "cleanText": [["first", "contrary", "to", "this", "court", "s", "admonition", "it", "quite", "literally", "constitutionalize", "the", "employee", "grievance", "process", "by", "supplant", "carefully", "calibrate", "nonconstitutional", "safeguard", "and", "by", "provide", "a", "potential", "first", "amendment", "claim", "in", "federal", "court", "to", "any", "employee", "who", "have", "file", "a", "grievance", "on", "a", "matter", "of", "only", "private", "interest"]]}, {"text": "And second--", "start": 1183.259, "stop": 1184.145, "duration": 0.89, "cleanText": [["and", "second"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "How much of your argument is premised on the fact that there was an alternative mechanism to the court system available.", "start": 1184.145, "stop": 1193.172, "duration": 9.03, "cleanText": [["how", "much", "of", "your", "argument", "be", "premise", "on", "the", "fact", "that", "there", "be", "an", "alternative", "mechanism", "to", "the", "court", "system", "available"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That certainly--", "start": 1193.172, "stop": 1194.186, "duration": 1.01, "cleanText": [["that", "certainly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Meaning let's assume there wasn't a collective bargaining agreement, let's assume there wasn't a State law protection, all of the items that you mention in your brief as existing to resolve disputes, that the only avenue for redress were the courts.", "start": 1194.186, "stop": 1208.94, "duration": 14.75, "cleanText": [["mean", "let", "us", "assume", "there", "be", "not", "a", "collective", "bargaining", "agreement", "let", "us", "assume", "there", "be", "not", "a", "state", "law", "protection", "all", "of", "the", "item", "that", "you", "mention", "in", "your", "brief", "as", "exist", "to", "resolve", "dispute", "that", "the", "only", "avenue", "for", "redress", "we", "be", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "So where would that put your argument?", "start": 1208.94, "stop": 1212.111, "duration": 3.17, "cleanText": [["so", "where", "would", "that", "put", "your", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, it's a hard hypothetical to answer, of course, because the grievance was filed pursuant to the collective bargaining agreement.", "start": 1212.111, "stop": 1217.701, "duration": 5.59, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "a", "hard", "hypothetical", "to", "answer", "of", "course", "because", "the", "grievance", "be", "file", "pursuant", "to", "the", "collective", "bargaining", "agreement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Putting it aside.", "start": 1217.701, "stop": 1218.196, "duration": 0.49, "cleanText": [["put", "it", "aside"]]}, {"text": "You -- you were talking about constitutionalizing a grievance process.", "start": 1218.196, "stop": 1224.22, "duration": 6.02, "cleanText": [["you", "you", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "constitutionalize", "a", "grievance", "process"]]}, {"text": "I'm going more broadly and saying how much of your argument depends on that fact?", "start": 1224.22, "stop": 1229.635, "duration": 5.41, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "go", "more", "broadly", "and", "say", "how", "much", "of", "your", "argument", "depend", "on", "that", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think that's an important part--", "start": 1229.635, "stop": 1230.941, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "that", "be", "an", "important", "part"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was the meaning would -- it is harder if all they have access to is a court proceeding.", "start": 1230.941, "stop": 1236.75, "duration": 5.81, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "meaning", "would", "it", "be", "hard", "if", "all", "they", "have", "access", "to", "be", "a", "court", "proceeding"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think that's an important part of the argument, for this reason: If you look at the Third Circuit's case in San Filippo, the court had a kind of a doctrinal basis for its ruling, but it also had a practical concern that not affording protection for this kind of petitioning activity would be a trap to the unwary.", "start": 1236.75, "stop": 1250.942, "duration": 14.19, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "an", "important", "part", "of", "the", "argument", "for", "this", "reason", "if", "you", "look", "at", "the", "third", "circuit", "s", "case", "in", "san", "filippo", "the", "court", "have", "a", "kind", "of", "a", "doctrinal", "basis", "for", "its", "ruling", "but", "it", "also", "have", "a", "practical", "concern", "that", "not", "afford", "protection", "for", "this", "kind", "of", "petitioning", "activity", "would", "be", "a", "trap", "to", "the", "unwary"]]}, {"text": "But there was really no basis for that concern, because the issue here is when a sovereign provides a remedial mechanism or enters into a collective bargaining agreement that provides a remedial mechanism--", "start": 1250.942, "stop": 1262.38, "duration": 11.44, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "really", "no", "basis", "for", "that", "concern", "because", "the", "issue", "here", "be", "when", "a", "sovereign", "provide", "a", "remedial", "mechanism", "or", "enters", "into", "a", "collective", "bargaining", "agreement", "that", "provide", "a", "remedial", "mechanism"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "How about if they don't?", "start": 1262.38, "stop": 1262.985, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["how", "about", "if", "they", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It typically -- well--", "start": 1262.985, "stop": 1265.54, "duration": 2.56, "cleanText": [["it", "typically", "well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "How about if they don't?", "start": 1265.54, "stop": 1266.379, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["how", "about", "if", "they", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "That's my point.", "start": 1266.379, "stop": 1267.284, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "my", "point"]]}, {"text": "Then what happens to the Third Circuit's definition?", "start": 1267.284, "stop": 1269.757, "duration": 2.47, "cleanText": [["then", "what", "happen", "to", "the", "third", "circuit", "s", "definition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, then I think the -- the result is the same, and -- and our position is you -- you still apply Connick, just as speech on matters of private concern is protected by the First Amendment, yet under Connick, an employee who engages in speech on a matter of private concern is not going to be protected in the employment context in all respects.", "start": 1269.757, "stop": 1289.864, "duration": 20.11, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "i", "think", "the", "the", "result", "be", "the", "same", "and", "and", "our", "position", "be", "you", "you", "still", "apply", "connick", "just", "as", "speech", "on", "matter", "of", "private", "concern", "be", "protect", "by", "the", "first", "amendment", "yet", "under", "connick", "an", "employee", "who", "engage", "in", "speech", "on", "a", "matter", "of", "private", "concern", "be", "not", "go", "to", "be", "protect", "in", "the", "employment", "context", "in", "all", "respect"]]}, {"text": "And that reflects a very important balance that this Court has struck between its view of how the Constitution applies to the government as sovereign regulator of the general public and how it applies to the government and its proprietary status as an employer.", "start": 1289.864, "stop": 1303.947, "duration": 14.08, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "reflect", "a", "very", "important", "balance", "that", "this", "court", "have", "strike", "between", "its", "view", "of", "how", "the", "constitution", "apply", "to", "the", "government", "as", "sovereign", "regulator", "of", "the", "general", "public", "and", "how", "it", "apply", "to", "the", "government", "and", "its", "proprietary", "status", "as", "an", "employer"]]}, {"text": "And in that latter situation, Connick has been critical in providing a bulwark against allowing run-of-the-mill employment disputes from becoming constitutional cases in Federal Court.", "start": 1303.947, "stop": 1315.822, "duration": 11.88, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "that", "latter", "situation", "connick", "have", "be", "critical", "in", "provide", "a", "bulwark", "against", "allow", "run", "of", "the", "mill", "employment", "dispute", "from", "become", "constitutional", "case", "in", "federal", "court"]]}, {"text": "And the second main problem with the Third Circuit's approach, and it's one that Mr. Ortiz highlighted, is that it privileges petition activity over speech activity, contrary to this Court's numerous statements that there is no such hierarchy in the First Amendment.", "start": 1315.822, "stop": 1332.663, "duration": 16.84, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "second", "main", "problem", "with", "the", "third", "circuit", "s", "approach", "and", "it", "be", "one", "that", "mr", "ortiz", "highlight", "be", "that", "it", "privilege", "petition", "activity", "over", "speech", "activity", "contrary", "to", "this", "court", "s", "numerous", "statement", "that", "there", "be", "no", "such", "hierarchy", "in", "the", "first", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "So going back to Thomas v. Collins in 1945, the Court called the two rights inseparable.", "start": 1332.663, "stop": 1337.983, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["so", "go", "back", "to", "thomas", "v", "collins", "in", "the", "court", "call", "the", "two", "right", "inseparable"]]}, {"text": "In the United Mine Workers case, which is a case relied on by the other side, it's an access to courts case, the Court interchangeably applied the speech right, the petition right, and the assembly right, and it said they were intimately connected in origin and purpose.", "start": 1337.983, "stop": 1351.087, "duration": 13.1, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "united", "mine", "worker", "case", "which", "be", "a", "case", "rely", "on", "by", "the", "other", "side", "it", "be", "an", "access", "to", "court", "case", "the", "court", "interchangeably", "apply", "the", "speech", "right", "the", "petition", "right", "and", "the", "assembly", "right", "and", "it", "say", "they", "we", "be", "intimately", "connect", "in", "origin", "and", "purpose"]]}, {"text": "And, of course--", "start": 1351.087, "stop": 1351.835, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["and", "of", "course"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Palmore -- I'm sorry.", "start": 1351.835, "stop": 1352.753, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["mr", "palmore", "I", "be", "sorry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, please.", "start": 1352.753, "stop": 1354.121, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["no", "please"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Suppose a State legislature passes a law depriving all State employees of collective bargaining rights, and a State employee files a lawsuit saying that this law violates the State constitution, and the State employee is thereupon fired.", "start": 1354.121, "stop": 1371.505, "duration": 17.38, "cleanText": [["suppose", "a", "state", "legislature", "pass", "a", "law", "deprive", "all", "state", "employee", "of", "collective", "bargaining", "right", "and", "a", "state", "employee", "file", "a", "lawsuit", "say", "that", "this", "law", "violate", "the", "state", "constitution", "and", "the", "state", "employee", "be", "thereupon", "fire"]]}, {"text": "Is that a matter of public concern or not?", "start": 1371.505, "stop": 1374.06, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "It -- it likely would be, and I think this -- this goes to some of the questions Justice Scalia was asking.", "start": 1374.06, "stop": 1379.491, "duration": 5.43, "cleanText": [["it", "it", "likely", "would", "be", "and", "i", "think", "this", "this", "go", "to", "some", "of", "the", "question", "justice", "scalia", "be", "ask"]]}, {"text": "But as this Court said in Connick that the question about -- of whether speech is a matter of public concern is assessed not only by the content, but by the form and the context.", "start": 1379.491, "stop": 1388.861, "duration": 9.37, "cleanText": [["but", "as", "this", "court", "say", "in", "connick", "that", "the", "question", "about", "of", "whether", "speech", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "be", "assess", "not", "only", "by", "the", "content", "but", "by", "the", "form", "and", "the", "context"]]}, {"text": "So in the case that Your Honor is positing, the content of the -- of the speech, which was that an act of the legislature was illegal, would suggest that it was a matter of public concern, the form, the form of a lawsuit is relevant to the consideration, and the context that it came in part of a larger political debate would likely be relevant, too.", "start": 1388.861, "stop": 1409.635, "duration": 20.77, "cleanText": [["so", "in", "the", "case", "that", "your", "honor", "be", "posit", "the", "content", "of", "the", "of", "the", "speech", "which", "be", "that", "an", "act", "of", "the", "legislature", "be", "illegal", "would", "suggest", "that", "it", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "the", "form", "the", "form", "of", "a", "lawsuit", "be", "relevant", "to", "the", "consideration", "and", "the", "context", "that", "it", "come", "in", "part", "of", "a", "large", "political", "debate", "would", "likely", "be", "relevant", "too"]]}, {"text": "The problem with the Third Circuit approach is that it never engages in that kind of inquiry.", "start": 1409.635, "stop": 1415.751, "duration": 6.12, "cleanText": [["the", "problem", "with", "the", "third", "circuit", "approach", "be", "that", "it", "never", "engage", "in", "that", "kind", "of", "inquiry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "And suppose -- now going back to Justice Sotomayor's example, suppose that there were a -- a class action alleging systemic discrimination in some governmental workplace.", "start": 1415.751, "stop": 1425.555, "duration": 9.8, "cleanText": [["and", "suppose", "now", "go", "back", "to", "justice", "sotomayor", "s", "example", "suppose", "that", "there", "we", "be", "a", "a", "class", "action", "allege", "systemic", "discrimination", "in", "some", "governmental", "workplace"]]}, {"text": "Would that be a matter of public concern?", "start": 1425.555, "stop": 1427.641, "duration": 2.09, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "It very well might be.", "start": 1427.641, "stop": 1429.291, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["it", "very", "well", "might", "be"]]}, {"text": "That's similar to this Court's decision in the GiVon case.", "start": 1429.291, "stop": 1432.326, "duration": 3.04, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "similar", "to", "this", "court", "s", "decision", "in", "the", "givon", "case"]]}, {"text": "So that was a case where a teacher went to complain to her principal about the school's general policy of discrimination, and this Court held that that was speech on a matter of public concern, that it affected more than just that individual employee's employment status.", "start": 1432.326, "stop": 1447.966, "duration": 15.64, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "be", "a", "case", "where", "a", "teacher", "go", "to", "complain", "to", "her", "principal", "about", "the", "school", "s", "general", "policy", "of", "discrimination", "and", "this", "court", "hold", "that", "that", "be", "speech", "on", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "that", "it", "affect", "more", "than", "just", "that", "individual", "employee", "s", "employment", "status"]]}, {"text": "So many of these hypotheticals and many submissions and petitions to the government as sovereign will, in fact, satisfy the public concern test, and then you'll get into Pickering balancing.", "start": 1447.966, "stop": 1461.896, "duration": 13.93, "cleanText": [["so", "many", "of", "these", "hypothetical", "and", "many", "submission", "and", "petition", "to", "the", "government", "as", "sovereign", "will", "in", "fact", "satisfy", "the", "public", "concern", "test", "and", "then", "you", "will", "get", "into", "pickering", "balancing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you -- can you think of any instance where speech by the employee would not be protected under the Pickering-Connick free speech calculus but would be protected under the Petition Clause?", "start": 1461.896, "stop": 1476.635, "duration": 14.74, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "can", "you", "think", "of", "any", "instance", "where", "speech", "by", "the", "employee", "would", "not", "be", "protect", "under", "the", "pickering", "connick", "free", "speech", "calculus", "but", "would", "be", "protect", "under", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that, no, if you put it in that way; this Court has never separately analyzed the two.", "start": 1476.635, "stop": 1483.996, "duration": 7.36, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "no", "if", "you", "put", "it", "in", "that", "way", "this", "court", "have", "never", "separately", "analyze", "the", "two"]]}, {"text": "But I think it is important to note that I think the Connick test already takes into account the distinction between what might be deemed petitioning conduct and non-petitioning conduct because of its use of the term \"form\".", "start": 1483.996, "stop": 1496.959, "duration": 12.96, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "it", "be", "important", "to", "note", "that", "i", "think", "the", "connick", "test", "already", "take", "into", "account", "the", "distinction", "between", "what", "might", "be", "deem", "petitioning", "conduct", "and", "non", "petitioning", "conduct", "because", "of", "its", "use", "of", "the", "term", "form"]]}, {"text": "So, again, the Connick test calls on courts to look on the content, the context and the form.", "start": 1496.959, "stop": 1502.331, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["so", "again", "the", "connick", "test", "call", "on", "court", "to", "look", "on", "the", "content", "the", "context", "and", "the", "form"]]}, {"text": "So if the form of an employee complaint takes the form of a lawsuit filed in Federal court, that's something that -- that should be taken into account.", "start": 1502.331, "stop": 1510.889, "duration": 8.56, "cleanText": [["so", "if", "the", "form", "of", "an", "employee", "complaint", "take", "the", "form", "of", "a", "lawsuit", "file", "in", "federal", "court", "that", "be", "something", "that", "that", "should", "be", "take", "into", "account"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "What -- wouldn't a -- a written letter to -- to the employer, the government employer, similarly be a petition?", "start": 1510.889, "stop": 1520.833, "duration": 9.94, "cleanText": [["what", "would", "not", "a", "a", "write", "letter", "to", "to", "the", "employer", "the", "government", "employer", "similarly", "be", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "Is a lawsuit any more of a petition, if indeed it is a petition at all, which I doubt?", "start": 1520.833, "stop": 1526.033, "duration": 5.2, "cleanText": [["be", "a", "lawsuit", "any", "more", "of", "a", "petition", "if", "indeed", "it", "be", "a", "petition", "at", "all", "which", "i", "doubt"]]}, {"text": "Surely filing a statement with the employer is a petition as well.", "start": 1526.033, "stop": 1532.787, "duration": 6.75, "cleanText": [["surely", "file", "a", "statement", "with", "the", "employer", "be", "a", "petition", "as", "well"]]}, {"text": "So how does the form make any difference?", "start": 1532.787, "stop": 1535.103, "duration": 2.32, "cleanText": [["so", "how", "do", "the", "form", "make", "any", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "I -- it's -- I think it's a serious question about whether a letter submitted to an employer as an employer, not as a sovereign, is a petition.", "start": 1535.103, "stop": 1543.682, "duration": 8.58, "cleanText": [["i", "it", "be", "i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "serious", "question", "about", "whether", "a", "letter", "submit", "to", "an", "employer", "as", "an", "employer", "not", "as", "a", "sovereign", "be", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "But that's the kind of line-drawing that the Third Circuit approach requires.", "start": 1543.682, "stop": 1547.509, "duration": 3.83, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "the", "kind", "of", "line", "draw", "that", "the", "third", "circuit", "approach", "require"]]}, {"text": "This Court has had a very broad conception of what counts as petitioning activity, so in Edwards v. South Carolina the Court said that a march to the grounds of the State capitol in South Carolina to protest segregation was an example of petitioning conduct in its most classic and pristine form.", "start": 1547.509, "stop": 1561.576, "duration": 14.07, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "have", "have", "a", "very", "broad", "conception", "of", "what", "count", "as", "petitioning", "activity", "so", "in", "edward", "v", "south", "carolina", "the", "court", "say", "that", "a", "march", "to", "the", "ground", "of", "the", "state", "capitol", "in", "south", "carolina", "to", "protest", "segregation", "be", "an", "example", "of", "petition", "conduct", "in", "its", "most", "classic", "and", "pristine", "form"]]}, {"text": "The Third Circuit doesn't -- doesn't count -- wouldn't count that as a petition for this purpose.", "start": 1561.576, "stop": 1567.225, "duration": 5.65, "cleanText": [["the", "third", "circuit", "do", "not", "do", "not", "count", "would", "not", "count", "that", "as", "a", "petition", "for", "this", "purpose"]]}, {"text": "It has kind of a gerrymandered view of what will count as a petition, basically a lawsuit and an employee grievance.", "start": 1567.225, "stop": 1573.576, "duration": 6.35, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "kind", "of", "a", "gerrymandered", "view", "of", "what", "will", "count", "as", "a", "petition", "basically", "a", "lawsuit", "and", "an", "employee", "grievance"]]}, {"text": "Now, the -- the approach followed by the majority of the circuits and the approach we advocate today doesn't require that kind of line-drawing, because whether, for example, the grievance filed in this case is a petition or not, it's certainly speech, and so we would agree that it's susceptible to analysis under the normal Connick v. Myers framework.", "start": 1573.576, "stop": 1591.412, "duration": 17.84, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "the", "approach", "follow", "by", "the", "majority", "of", "the", "circuit", "and", "the", "approach", "we", "advocate", "today", "do", "not", "require", "that", "kind", "of", "line", "drawing", "because", "whether", "for", "example", "the", "grievance", "file", "in", "this", "case", "be", "a", "petition", "or", "not", "it", "be", "certainly", "speech", "and", "so", "we", "would", "agree", "that", "it", "be", "susceptible", "to", "analysis", "under", "the", "normal", "connick", "v", "myers", "framework"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Palmore, what about the distinction that the other side brings up that Connick is about what happens inside the workplace -- you don't want to disrupt the routine by the kind of activity in which Myers was involved -- but the Petition Clause, they're talking about conduct outside the workplace, that is a complaint filed in court, nothing that's happening in the workplace.", "start": 1591.412, "stop": 1624.404, "duration": 32.99, "cleanText": [["mr", "palmore", "what", "about", "the", "distinction", "that", "the", "other", "side", "bring", "up", "that", "connick", "be", "about", "what", "happen", "inside", "the", "workplace", "you", "do", "not", "want", "to", "disrupt", "the", "routine", "by", "the", "kind", "of", "activity", "in", "which", "myers", "be", "involve", "but", "the", "petition", "clause", "they", "be", "talk", "about", "conduct", "outside", "the", "workplace", "that", "be", "a", "complaint", "file", "in", "court", "nothing", "that", "be", "happen", "in", "the", "workplace"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think it's workplace-related and I think that's the test.", "start": 1624.404, "stop": 1629.088, "duration": 4.68, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "it", "be", "workplace", "related", "and", "i", "think", "that", "be", "the", "test"]]}, {"text": "So I don't think it -- you know, where an employee physically was when he or she filed the petition isn't really relevant.", "start": 1629.088, "stop": 1638.49, "duration": 9.4, "cleanText": [["so", "i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "you", "know", "where", "an", "employee", "physically", "be", "when", "he", "or", "she", "file", "the", "petition", "be", "not", "really", "relevant"]]}, {"text": "The question is the connection to the workplace and the connection to the employer-employee relationship.", "start": 1638.49, "stop": 1644.076, "duration": 5.59, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "be", "the", "connection", "to", "the", "workplace", "and", "the", "connection", "to", "the", "employer", "employee", "relationship"]]}, {"text": "So as Mr. Ortiz answered before, the NTEU case provides a separate set of protections under the First Amendment, under the speech protection for employees who engage in speech conduct that has no connection to the workplace, and it would limit the ability of a government employer to take action against such an employee.", "start": 1644.076, "stop": 1661.35, "duration": 17.27, "cleanText": [["so", "as", "mr", "ortiz", "answer", "before", "the", "nteu", "case", "provide", "a", "separate", "set", "of", "protection", "under", "the", "first", "amendment", "under", "the", "speech", "protection", "for", "employee", "who", "engage", "in", "speech", "conduct", "that", "have", "no", "connection", "to", "the", "workplace", "and", "it", "would", "limit", "the", "ability", "of", "a", "government", "employer", "to", "take", "action", "against", "such", "an", "employee"]]}, {"text": "But the conduct here is the -- the grievances that were filed here were obviously intimately connected to the workplace relationship between Chief Guarnieri and the Borough Council.", "start": 1661.35, "stop": 1671.185, "duration": 9.84, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "conduct", "here", "be", "the", "the", "grievance", "that", "we", "be", "file", "here", "we", "be", "obviously", "intimately", "connect", "to", "the", "workplace", "relationship", "between", "chief", "guarnieri", "and", "the", "borough", "council"]]}, {"text": "This was not a case like NTEU, where someone wanted to go out and give a speech on something that had no connection to their job or go out and file a lawsuit or some kind of petitioning activity on something that had no connection to the workplace.", "start": 1671.185, "stop": 1685.829, "duration": 14.64, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "not", "a", "case", "like", "nteu", "where", "someone", "want", "to", "go", "out", "and", "give", "a", "speech", "on", "something", "that", "have", "no", "connection", "to", "their", "job", "or", "go", "out", "and", "file", "a", "lawsuit", "or", "some", "kind", "of", "petition", "activity", "on", "something", "that", "have", "no", "connection", "to", "the", "workplace"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Palmore, on that matter, one last hypothetical.", "start": 1685.829, "stop": 1688.212, "duration": 2.38, "cleanText": [["mr", "palmore", "on", "that", "matter", "one", "last", "hypothetical"]]}, {"text": "Suppose the New York City council passed a resolution that said a precinct house would be closed all night long from 7 p.m. to 7 a.m., and the chief of -- of that precinct filed suit saying that this was micromanagement and it was going to affect the public safety of the citizenry, and then that chief of police was fired.", "start": 1688.212, "stop": 1711.838, "duration": 23.63, "cleanText": [["suppose", "the", "new", "york", "city", "council", "pass", "a", "resolution", "that", "say", "a", "precinct", "house", "would", "be", "close", "all", "night", "long", "from", "pm", "to", "am", "and", "the", "chief", "of", "of", "that", "precinct", "file", "suit", "say", "that", "this", "be", "micromanagement", "and", "it", "be", "go", "to", "affect", "the", "public", "safety", "of", "the", "citizenry", "and", "then", "that", "chief", "of", "police", "be", "fire"]]}, {"text": "Is that a matter of public concern?", "start": 1711.838, "stop": 1713.379, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "It very well might be.", "start": 1713.379, "stop": 1714.857, "duration": 1.48, "cleanText": [["it", "very", "well", "might", "be"]]}, {"text": "It's hard to answer in the abstract, because what this Court has said is that the question has to be analyzed in light of the whole record and in light of the context -- content, the context, and the form.", "start": 1714.857, "stop": 1723.634, "duration": 8.78, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "hard", "to", "answer", "in", "the", "abstract", "because", "what", "this", "court", "have", "say", "be", "that", "the", "question", "have", "to", "be", "analyze", "in", "light", "of", "the", "whole", "record", "and", "in", "light", "of", "the", "context", "content", "the", "context", "and", "the", "form"]]}, {"text": "It's not necessary for this Court in this case to decide whether the petitioning and speech activity here was on a matter of public or private concern.", "start": 1723.634, "stop": 1730.875, "duration": 7.24, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "necessary", "for", "this", "court", "in", "this", "case", "to", "decide", "whether", "the", "petitioning", "and", "speech", "activity", "here", "be", "on", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "or", "private", "concern"]]}, {"text": "The question presented says that it was on a matter of private concern.", "start": 1730.875, "stop": 1733.817, "duration": 2.94, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "present", "say", "that", "it", "be", "on", "a", "matter", "of", "private", "concern"]]}, {"text": "So all the Court needs to decide is -- is whether that makes a difference or not in terms of the constitutional analysis.", "start": 1733.817, "stop": 1739.718, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["so", "all", "the", "court", "need", "to", "decide", "be", "be", "whether", "that", "make", "a", "difference", "or", "not", "in", "term", "of", "the", "constitutional", "analysis"]]}, {"text": "And then the Third Circuit on remand could -- could decide, assuming the arguments were preserved, could look at the whole record and decide whether the speech activity here was on a matter of public or private concern.", "start": 1739.718, "stop": 1750.314, "duration": 10.6, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "the", "third", "circuit", "on", "remand", "could", "could", "decide", "assume", "the", "argument", "we", "be", "preserve", "could", "look", "at", "the", "whole", "record", "and", "decide", "whether", "the", "speech", "activity", "here", "be", "on", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "or", "private", "concern"]]}, {"text": "If there are no further questions, we ask the judgment be reversed.", "start": 1750.314, "stop": 1755.451, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "no", "further", "question", "we", "ask", "the", "judgment", "be", "reverse"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, counsel.", "start": 1755.451, "stop": 1756.384, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "counsel"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Schnapper.", "start": 1756.384, "stop": 1760.012, "duration": 3.63, "cleanText": [["mr", "schnapper"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 1760.012, "stop": 1761.783, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Neither the text, history, or purpose of the Petition Clause nor the interest of a government employer in an efficient workplace provide a basis for distinguishing and giving less protection to a petition because it didn't involve a matter of public concern.", "start": 1761.783, "stop": 1778.125, "duration": 16.34, "cleanText": [["neither", "the", "text", "history", "or", "purpose", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "nor", "the", "interest", "of", "a", "government", "employer", "in", "an", "efficient", "workplace", "provide", "a", "basis", "for", "distinguish", "and", "give", "less", "protection", "to", "a", "petition", "because", "it", "do", "not", "involve", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}, {"text": "The text of the Petition Clause certainly draws no such distinction.", "start": 1778.125, "stop": 1783.914, "duration": 5.79, "cleanText": [["the", "text", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "certainly", "draw", "no", "such", "distinction"]]}, {"text": "The subject of the petition must be a grievance and a grievance I think is measured by whether the matter is of concern to the petitioner.", "start": 1783.914, "stop": 1791.915, "duration": 8, "cleanText": [["the", "subject", "of", "the", "petition", "must", "be", "a", "grievance", "and", "a", "grievance", "i", "think", "be", "measure", "by", "whether", "the", "matter", "be", "of", "concern", "to", "the", "petitioner"]]}, {"text": "If it's a problem of concern to the petitioner, that satisfies that constitutional element.", "start": 1791.915, "stop": 1797.658, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "be", "a", "problem", "of", "concern", "to", "the", "petitioner", "that", "satisfy", "that", "constitutional", "element"]]}, {"text": "It does not matter whether the public cares a lot, it doesn't care--", "start": 1797.658, "stop": 1801.469, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "matter", "whether", "the", "public", "care", "a", "lot", "it", "do", "not", "care"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "But all of our cases have equated the Petition Clause reach with that of the First Amendment, and our cases under the First Amendment have made clear that we don't want to constitutionalize the -- the employee grievance procedures.", "start": 1801.469, "stop": 1814.869, "duration": 13.4, "cleanText": [["but", "all", "of", "our", "case", "have", "equate", "the", "petition", "clause", "reach", "with", "that", "of", "the", "first", "amendment", "and", "our", "case", "under", "the", "first", "amendment", "have", "make", "clear", "that", "we", "do", "not", "want", "to", "constitutionalize", "the", "the", "employee", "grievance", "procedure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, with all respect, Mr. Chief Justice, I don't think this Court is committed to the view that the Petition Clause and the Free Speech Clause cover exactly the same things.", "start": 1814.869, "stop": 1825.905, "duration": 11.04, "cleanText": [["well", "with", "all", "respect", "mr", "chief", "justice", "i", "do", "not", "think", "this", "court", "be", "commit", "to", "the", "view", "that", "the", "petition", "clause", "and", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "cover", "exactly", "the", "same", "thing"]]}, {"text": "In fact, emphatically they -- obviously they don't because the Free Speech Clause covers many things that the Petition Clause would not.", "start": 1825.905, "stop": 1831.987, "duration": 6.08, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "emphatically", "they", "obviously", "they", "do", "not", "because", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "cover", "many", "thing", "that", "the", "petition", "clause", "would", "not"]]}, {"text": "It covered, for example, the remark--", "start": 1831.987, "stop": 1833.949, "duration": 1.96, "cleanText": [["it", "cover", "for", "example", "the", "remark"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Does the Petition Clause cover anything that the First Amendment does not?", "start": 1833.949, "stop": 1837.609, "duration": 3.66, "cleanText": [["do", "the", "petition", "clause", "cover", "anything", "that", "the", "first", "amendment", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I believe so, Your Honor.", "start": 1837.609, "stop": 1839.146, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "so", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "This Court's decisions in the antitrust area and under the National Labor Relations Act with regard to -- an -- access to the government or -- or the courts, they've always been framed solely in terms of the Petition Clause, not the Free Speech Clause.", "start": 1839.146, "stop": 1854.961, "duration": 15.82, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "s", "decision", "in", "the", "antitrust", "area", "and", "under", "the", "national", "labor", "relation", "act", "with", "regard", "to", "an", "access", "to", "the", "government", "or", "or", "the", "court", "they", "have", "always", "be", "frame", "solely", "in", "term", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "not", "the", "free", "speech", "clause"]]}, {"text": "It would be at least very awkward to characterize those -- those problems as free speech cases, particularly where, as is typically the case, the -- the underlying activity was on the part of, say, a lawyer rather than an individual who -- who is asserting the petition right.", "start": 1854.961, "stop": 1874.739, "duration": 19.78, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "be", "at", "least", "very", "awkward", "to", "characterize", "those", "those", "problem", "as", "free", "speech", "case", "particularly", "where", "as", "be", "typically", "the", "case", "the", "the", "underlying", "activity", "be", "on", "the", "part", "of", "say", "a", "lawyer", "rather", "than", "an", "individual", "who", "who", "be", "assert", "the", "petition", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, getting back to the second part of my question--", "start": 1874.739, "stop": 1878.18, "duration": 3.44, "cleanText": [["well", "get", "back", "to", "the", "second", "part", "of", "my", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1878.18, "stop": 1878.539, "duration": 0.36, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--in the First Amendment cases we were concerned about, as I said, constitutionalizing employee grievances.", "start": 1878.539, "stop": 1885.136, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "first", "amendment", "case", "we", "we", "be", "concern", "about", "as", "i", "say", "constitutionalize", "employee", "grievance"]]}, {"text": "If you constitutionalize it under the Petition Clause, how is that any less a problem of constitutionalizing it under the First Amendment?", "start": 1885.136, "stop": 1891.829, "duration": 6.69, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "constitutionalize", "it", "under", "the", "petition", "clause", "how", "be", "that", "any", "less", "a", "problem", "of", "constitutionalize", "it", "under", "the", "first", "amendment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it -- it's our view, Mr. Chief Justice, that -- and in this respect to some extent I think we agree with a statement made by Petitioners -- that every gripe that an individual employee might have, indeed most of them, wouldn't be covered by the Petition Clause.", "start": 1891.829, "stop": 1908.042, "duration": 16.21, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "it", "be", "our", "view", "mr", "chief", "justice", "that", "and", "in", "this", "respect", "to", "some", "extent", "i", "think", "we", "agree", "with", "a", "statement", "make", "by", "petitioner", "that", "every", "gripe", "that", "an", "individual", "employee", "might", "have", "indeed", "most", "of", "them", "would", "not", "be", "cover", "by", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "In the petition reply brief, the Petitioners state, and we agree with this, that the ordinary, routine e-mails, give and take within the office, that's not covered by the Petition Clause.", "start": 1908.042, "stop": 1917.382, "duration": 9.34, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "petition", "reply", "brief", "the", "petitioner", "state", "and", "we", "agree", "with", "this", "that", "the", "ordinary", "routine", "e", "mail", "give", "and", "take", "within", "the", "office", "that", "be", "not", "cover", "by", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "We would agree with that.", "start": 1917.382, "stop": 1917.772, "duration": 0.39, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "agree", "with", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "All you have to do then is add a sentence to your complaint saying: This is an example of how the government employer mistreats its employees?", "start": 1917.772, "stop": 1924.497, "duration": 6.73, "cleanText": [["all", "you", "have", "to", "do", "then", "be", "add", "a", "sentence", "to", "your", "complaint", "say", "this", "be", "an", "example", "of", "how", "the", "government", "employer", "mistreat", "its", "employee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 1924.497, "stop": 1926.147, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "And then it becomes more generalized?", "start": 1926.147, "stop": 1927.469, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "it", "become", "more", "generalize"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no, Your Honor.", "start": 1927.469, "stop": 1928.916, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["no", "no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "That -- that -- that's their view, that -- that it becomes a matter of public concern if you say it affects a lot of people.", "start": 1928.916, "stop": 1933.197, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["that", "that", "that", "be", "their", "view", "that", "that", "it", "become", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "if", "you", "say", "it", "affect", "a", "lot", "of", "people"]]}, {"text": "Our view is that that's not relevant.", "start": 1933.197, "stop": 1934.956, "duration": 1.76, "cleanText": [["our", "view", "be", "that", "that", "be", "not", "relevant"]]}, {"text": "It--", "start": 1934.956, "stop": 1936.716, "duration": 1.76, "cleanText": [["it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if added to that is \"and I'm going to sue\" or", "start": 1936.716, "stop": 1940.714, "duration": 4, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "add", "to", "that", "be", "and", "I", "be", "go", "to", "sue", "or"]]}, {"text": "\"I'm going to file a grievance? \"", "start": 1940.714, "stop": 1942.52, "duration": 1.81, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "go", "to", "file", "a", "grievance"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, Your Honor, saying that wouldn't have that effect.", "start": 1942.52, "stop": 1947.205, "duration": 4.68, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor", "say", "that", "would", "not", "have", "that", "effect"]]}, {"text": "The case to which they refer is one in which an employee indicated, as indeed occurred, that he was going to file a lawsuit, and the employer retaliated in a peremptory fashion because of that.", "start": 1947.205, "stop": 1960.2, "duration": 13, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "to", "which", "they", "refer", "be", "one", "in", "which", "an", "employee", "indicate", "as", "indeed", "occur", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "file", "a", "lawsuit", "and", "the", "employer", "retaliate", "in", "a", "peremptory", "fashion", "because", "of", "that"]]}, {"text": "That -- that's been the rule in the Third Circuit, it has only come up twice, but if I might point out, that's the rule under any -- any number of Federal statutes which protect filing a charge with the EEOC or filing a lawsuit.", "start": 1960.2, "stop": 1975.703, "duration": 15.5, "cleanText": [["that", "that", "be", "be", "the", "rule", "in", "the", "third", "circuit", "it", "have", "only", "come", "up", "twice", "but", "if", "i", "might", "point", "out", "that", "be", "the", "rule", "under", "any", "any", "number", "of", "federal", "statute", "which", "protect", "file", "a", "charge", "with", "the", "eeoc", "or", "file", "a", "lawsuit"]]}, {"text": "The lower courts have agreed--", "start": 1975.703, "stop": 1976.853, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["the", "low", "court", "have", "agree"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, under -- under the First Amendment speech clause--", "start": 1976.853, "stop": 1980.341, "duration": 3.49, "cleanText": [["well", "under", "under", "the", "first", "amendment", "speech", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 1980.341, "stop": 1981.57, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "--We have said that an employee's, public employee's, right to speech can be regulated, can be confined, can be restricted beyond what the State could do for a nonemployee.", "start": 1981.57, "stop": 1992.712, "duration": 11.14, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "say", "that", "an", "employee", "s", "public", "employee", "s", "right", "to", "speech", "can", "be", "regulate", "can", "be", "confine", "can", "be", "restrict", "beyond", "what", "the", "state", "could", "do", "for", "a", "nonemployee"]]}, {"text": "Are you saying that if -- if the Petition Clause is involved there is no right to restrict what the -- employer does?", "start": 1992.712, "stop": 2000.358, "duration": 7.65, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "say", "that", "if", "if", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "involve", "there", "be", "no", "right", "to", "restrict", "what", "the", "employer", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor.", "start": 2000.358, "stop": 2001.634, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "The government--", "start": 2001.634, "stop": 2002.274, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["the", "government"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then you have to offer a test and you don't want the public concern test, so what's your test?", "start": 2002.274, "stop": 2006.366, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["then", "you", "have", "to", "offer", "a", "test", "and", "you", "do", "not", "want", "the", "public", "concern", "test", "so", "what", "be", "your", "test"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The, the -- that it, the government's interest as an employer is part of the calculus if -- if this issue arose under the Petition Clause, and under ordinary balancing one would look at the nature of the government's interest and the degree of burden that's imposed, and that's the way the Court has administered the Petition Clause.", "start": 2006.366, "stop": 2033.459, "duration": 27.09, "cleanText": [["the", "the", "that", "it", "the", "government", "s", "interest", "as", "an", "employer", "be", "part", "of", "the", "calculus", "if", "if", "this", "issue", "arise", "under", "the", "petition", "clause", "and", "under", "ordinary", "balance", "one", "would", "look", "at", "the", "nature", "of", "the", "government", "s", "interest", "and", "the", "degree", "of", "burden", "that", "be", "impose", "and", "that", "be", "the", "way", "the", "court", "have", "administer", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you would be content to apply that analytic, broad analytic framework to the Petition Clause?", "start": 2033.459, "stop": 2038.159, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "would", "be", "content", "to", "apply", "that", "analytic", "broad", "analytic", "framework", "to", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, that's what the Court has done.", "start": 2038.159, "stop": 2041.21, "duration": 3.05, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "have", "what", "the", "court", "have", "do"]]}, {"text": "Now, that said, I think there are circumstances where the government would be hard pressed to argue that it had a generalized interest in stopping a particular form of petition.", "start": 2041.21, "stop": 2052.882, "duration": 11.67, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "say", "i", "think", "there", "be", "circumstance", "where", "the", "government", "would", "be", "hard", "press", "to", "argue", "that", "it", "have", "a", "generalized", "interest", "in", "stop", "a", "particular", "form", "of", "petition"]]}, {"text": "For example, the Petitioners express a considerable unhappiness that they're subject to suit under section 1983.", "start": 2052.882, "stop": 2061.332, "duration": 8.45, "cleanText": [["for", "example", "the", "petitioner", "express", "a", "considerable", "unhappiness", "that", "they", "be", "subject", "to", "suit", "under", "section"]]}, {"text": "It's expensive, it requires lawyers, they could have to pay counsel fees.", "start": 2061.332, "stop": 2064.867, "duration": 3.54, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "expensive", "it", "require", "lawyer", "they", "could", "have", "to", "pay", "counsel", "fee"]]}, {"text": "Those are judgments that the Congress of the United States made in 1871 when it adopted section 1983.", "start": 2064.867, "stop": 2071.229, "duration": 6.36, "cleanText": [["those", "be", "judgment", "that", "the", "congress", "of", "the", "united", "state", "make", "in", "when", "it", "adopt", "section"]]}, {"text": "It knew the government was -- local governments would be subject to it.", "start": 2071.229, "stop": 2073.706, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["it", "know", "the", "government", "be", "local", "government", "would", "be", "subject", "to", "it"]]}, {"text": "When the Congress strikes that balance, and -- and of course, section 1983 is a very complicated piece of machinery -- the balance Congress struck is -- is ordinarily going to be controlling--", "start": 2073.706, "stop": 2085.889, "duration": 12.18, "cleanText": [["when", "the", "congress", "strike", "that", "balance", "and", "and", "of", "course", "section", "be", "a", "very", "complicated", "piece", "of", "machinery", "the", "balance", "congress", "struck", "be", "be", "ordinarily", "go", "to", "be", "control"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, let's talk about it.", "start": 2085.889, "stop": 2087.851, "duration": 1.96, "cleanText": [["well", "let", "us", "talk", "about", "it"]]}, {"text": "I find it difficult to believe that lawsuits are covered by the Petition Clause when it is very clear that the Congress can prevent all lawsuits against the Federal Government by simply refusing to waive sovereign immunity.", "start": 2087.851, "stop": 2107.322, "duration": 19.47, "cleanText": [["i", "find", "it", "difficult", "to", "believe", "that", "lawsuit", "be", "cover", "by", "the", "petition", "clause", "when", "it", "be", "very", "clear", "that", "the", "congress", "can", "prevent", "all", "lawsuit", "against", "the", "federal", "government", "by", "simply", "refuse", "to", "waive", "sovereign", "immunity"]]}, {"text": "Now, you know, how can you have a constitutional guarantee of the right to petition the government, which you say includes the -- the right to -- to be in law court, and yet the Federal Government can exempt itself from suits in law courts?", "start": 2107.322, "stop": 2122.263, "duration": 14.94, "cleanText": [["now", "you", "know", "how", "can", "you", "have", "a", "constitutional", "guarantee", "of", "the", "right", "to", "petition", "the", "government", "which", "you", "say", "include", "the", "the", "right", "to", "to", "be", "in", "law", "court", "and", "yet", "the", "federal", "government", "can", "exempt", "itself", "from", "suit", "in", "law", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, the -- the Federal Government is not obligated to provide a -- a lower court system for -- authorized to hear suits against it.", "start": 2122.263, "stop": 2133.029, "duration": 10.77, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "the", "the", "federal", "government", "be", "not", "obligate", "to", "provide", "a", "a", "low", "court", "system", "for", "authorize", "to", "hear", "suit", "against", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm not talking about just a lower court system.", "start": 2133.029, "stop": 2134.743, "duration": 1.71, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "talk", "about", "just", "a", "low", "court", "system"]]}, {"text": "I'm talking about all suits, right up to the Supreme Court.", "start": 2134.743, "stop": 2138.461, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "talk", "about", "all", "suit", "right", "up", "to", "the", "supreme", "court"]]}, {"text": "The Federal Government can say: You can't sue us.", "start": 2138.461, "stop": 2140.578, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["the", "federal", "government", "can", "say", "you", "can", "not", "sue", "us"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "It can.", "start": 2140.578, "stop": 2141.293, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["it", "can"]]}, {"text": "But it cannot set up a court system and then punish government employees for using it.", "start": 2141.293, "stop": 2146.165, "duration": 4.87, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "can", "not", "set", "up", "a", "court", "system", "and", "then", "punish", "government", "employee", "for", "use", "it"]]}, {"text": "They are not -- historic -- if I might step back a couple hundred years here, the--", "start": 2146.165, "stop": 2152.099, "duration": 5.93, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "not", "historic", "if", "i", "might", "step", "back", "a", "couple", "hundred", "year", "here", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "You're saying that the Petition Clause only covers those petitions that the government chooses to allow; is -- is that what the constitutional guarantee is?", "start": 2152.099, "stop": 2162.71, "duration": 10.61, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "say", "that", "the", "petition", "clause", "only", "cover", "those", "petition", "that", "the", "government", "choose", "to", "allow", "be", "be", "that", "what", "the", "constitutional", "guarantee", "be"]]}, {"text": "If you choose to allow a certain kind of petition, it is constitutionally guaranteed.", "start": 2162.71, "stop": 2170.85, "duration": 8.14, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "choose", "to", "allow", "a", "certain", "kind", "of", "petition", "it", "be", "constitutionally", "guarantee"]]}, {"text": "That's not much of a guarantee.", "start": 2170.85, "stop": 2173.573, "duration": 2.72, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "much", "of", "a", "guarantee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, I think -- I think historically that -- that's a fairly accurate description of what has happened with the emergence of the Petition Clause over the last 6 or 700 years of Anglo-American history.", "start": 2173.573, "stop": 2184.403, "duration": 10.83, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "think", "i", "think", "historically", "that", "that", "be", "a", "fairly", "accurate", "description", "of", "what", "have", "happen", "with", "the", "emergence", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "over", "the", "last", "or", "year", "of", "anglo", "american", "history"]]}, {"text": "There were no courts to which people could seek redress against the crown at the time of Magna Carta.", "start": 2184.403, "stop": 2191.082, "duration": 6.68, "cleanText": [["there", "we", "be", "no", "court", "to", "which", "people", "could", "seek", "redress", "against", "the", "crown", "at", "the", "time", "of", "magna", "carta"]]}, {"text": "Over time the courts became available to do that.", "start": 2191.082, "stop": 2194.429, "duration": 3.35, "cleanText": [["over", "time", "the", "court", "become", "available", "to", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "Insofar as they did, on our view, the Petition Clause would now apply.", "start": 2194.429, "stop": 2199.656, "duration": 5.23, "cleanText": [["insofar", "as", "they", "do", "on", "our", "view", "the", "petition", "clause", "would", "now", "apply"]]}, {"text": "And if I might turn to a question you asked earlier.", "start": 2199.656, "stop": 2201.957, "duration": 2.3, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "i", "might", "turn", "to", "a", "question", "you", "ask", "earlier"]]}, {"text": "You expressed some skepticism about whether the Petition Clause applies to lawsuits.", "start": 2201.957, "stop": 2207.825, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["you", "express", "some", "skepticism", "about", "whether", "the", "petition", "clause", "applies", "to", "lawsuit"]]}, {"text": "I note that in at least half a dozen decisions that this Court has held that, and I think that was the premise of your concurring opinion in the BE & K Construction case a few years ago.", "start": 2207.825, "stop": 2219.809, "duration": 11.98, "cleanText": [["i", "note", "that", "in", "at", "least", "half", "a", "dozen", "decision", "that", "this", "court", "have", "hold", "that", "and", "i", "think", "that", "be", "the", "premise", "of", "your", "concur", "opinion", "in", "the", "be", "k", "construction", "case", "a", "few", "year", "ago"]]}, {"text": "And we don't in this regard have to get deeply into history in the debate about whether courts are covered.", "start": 2219.809, "stop": 2226.64, "duration": 6.83, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "do", "not", "in", "this", "regard", "have", "to", "get", "deeply", "into", "history", "in", "the", "debate", "about", "whether", "court", "be", "cover"]]}, {"text": "The text of the First -- of the Petition Clause is sufficient on its face.", "start": 2226.64, "stop": 2230.674, "duration": 4.03, "cleanText": [["the", "text", "of", "the", "first", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "sufficient", "on", "its", "face"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't say petitions to the legislature.", "start": 2230.674, "stop": 2233.615, "duration": 2.94, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "say", "petition", "to", "the", "legislature"]]}, {"text": "It says petitions to the government, and that was clearly a deliberate choice, because the States--", "start": 2233.615, "stop": 2238.546, "duration": 4.93, "cleanText": [["it", "say", "petition", "to", "the", "government", "and", "that", "be", "clearly", "a", "deliberate", "choice", "because", "the", "state"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Schnapper, you can write a letter to the president, you can write a letter to your congressional representative, but getting to a court, you have to pay a filing fee.", "start": 2238.546, "stop": 2248.725, "duration": 10.18, "cleanText": [["mr", "schnapper", "you", "can", "write", "a", "letter", "to", "the", "president", "you", "can", "write", "a", "letter", "to", "your", "congressional", "representative", "but", "get", "to", "a", "court", "you", "have", "to", "pay", "a", "filing", "fee"]]}, {"text": "And since this would be a civil case, this Court has held if you haven't got whatever is the filing fee amount, too bad, you don't have access to the Court.", "start": 2248.725, "stop": 2260.958, "duration": 12.23, "cleanText": [["and", "since", "this", "would", "be", "a", "civil", "case", "this", "court", "have", "hold", "if", "you", "have", "not", "get", "whatever", "be", "the", "filing", "fee", "amount", "too", "bad", "you", "do", "not", "have", "access", "to", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, Your Honor, and I think those cases are clearly distinguishable.", "start": 2260.958, "stop": 2264.893, "duration": 3.93, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "and", "i", "think", "those", "case", "be", "clearly", "distinguishable"]]}, {"text": "The -- the core historical purpose of concern of the Petition Clause was reprisals by the government against people for -- for petitioning the government.", "start": 2264.893, "stop": 2276.054, "duration": 11.16, "cleanText": [["the", "the", "core", "historical", "purpose", "of", "concern", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "reprisal", "by", "the", "government", "against", "people", "for", "for", "petition", "the", "government"]]}, {"text": "There's a fundamental difference here between what's at stake here, where the Borough is asserting a right to punish people for going to court, and the question about whether the government has an affirmative obligation to remove the incidental barriers that may exist to bringing lawsuits.", "start": 2276.054, "stop": 2293.996, "duration": 17.94, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "a", "fundamental", "difference", "here", "between", "what", "be", "at", "stake", "here", "where", "the", "borough", "be", "assert", "a", "right", "to", "punish", "people", "for", "go", "to", "court", "and", "the", "question", "about", "whether", "the", "government", "have", "an", "affirmative", "obligation", "to", "remove", "the", "incidental", "barrier", "that", "may", "exist", "to", "bring", "lawsuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you -- do you think--", "start": 2293.996, "stop": 2295.088, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "do", "you", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "And so, we think those cases are distinguishable.", "start": 2295.088, "stop": 2296.349, "duration": 1.26, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "we", "think", "those", "case", "be", "distinguishable"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are you suggesting that in one of these suits you wouldn't have to pay the filing fee?", "start": 2296.349, "stop": 2300.456, "duration": 4.11, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "suggest", "that", "in", "one", "of", "these", "suit", "you", "would", "not", "have", "to", "pay", "the", "filing", "fee"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no, precisely to the contrary.", "start": 2300.456, "stop": 2303.351, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["no", "no", "precisely", "to", "the", "contrary"]]}, {"text": "We are asserting only that the government cannot punish Mr. Guarnieri for filing a lawsuit.", "start": 2303.351, "stop": 2308.238, "duration": 4.89, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "assert", "only", "that", "the", "government", "can", "not", "punish", "mr", "guarnieri", "for", "file", "a", "lawsuit"]]}, {"text": "We are not suggesting the government has to pay his filing fee, any more than if -- if the -- if Mr. Guarnieri wants to go to Harrisburg and meet with his or her representative, the government, our view, Duryea, can't punish him for doing it, but they don't have to give him gas money, and if he doesn't have enough money for gas that's just too bad.", "start": 2308.238, "stop": 2330.276, "duration": 22.04, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "not", "suggest", "the", "government", "have", "to", "pay", "his", "file", "fee", "any", "more", "than", "if", "if", "the", "if", "mr", "guarnieri", "want", "to", "go", "to", "harrisburg", "and", "meet", "with", "his", "or", "her", "representative", "the", "government", "our", "view", "duryea", "can", "not", "punish", "him", "for", "do", "it", "but", "they", "do", "not", "have", "to", "give", "him", "gas", "money", "and", "if", "he", "do", "not", "have", "enough", "money", "for", "gas", "that", "be", "just", "too", "bad"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Suppose the Borough here bought something from a company under a contract that included an arbitration clause.", "start": 2330.276, "stop": 2337.84, "duration": 7.56, "cleanText": [["suppose", "the", "borough", "here", "buy", "something", "from", "a", "company", "under", "a", "contract", "that", "include", "an", "arbitration", "clause"]]}, {"text": "Would that, would the right of the company to engage in arbitration be protected by the Petition Clause?", "start": 2337.84, "stop": 2345.682, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "would", "the", "right", "of", "the", "company", "to", "engage", "in", "arbitration", "be", "protect", "by", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 2345.682, "stop": 2348.825, "duration": 3.14, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "The -- we believe the Petition Clause applies to government-created mechanisms for redressing grievances; and if the government sets up an arbitration procedure like that, we think that that's covered.", "start": 2348.825, "stop": 2362.724, "duration": 13.9, "cleanText": [["the", "we", "believe", "the", "petition", "clause", "applies", "to", "government", "create", "mechanism", "for", "redress", "grievance", "and", "if", "the", "government", "set", "up", "an", "arbitration", "procedure", "like", "that", "we", "think", "that", "that", "be", "cover"]]}, {"text": "An arbitration agreement between two private parties would not be, be covered by the Petition Clause, because the government wouldn't have been involved in standing that up.", "start": 2362.724, "stop": 2371.564, "duration": 8.84, "cleanText": [["an", "arbitration", "agreement", "between", "two", "private", "party", "would", "not", "be", "be", "cover", "by", "the", "petition", "clause", "because", "the", "government", "would", "not", "have", "be", "involve", "in", "stand", "that", "up"]]}, {"text": "And that distinction really has its roots in history.", "start": 2371.564, "stop": 2374.444, "duration": 2.88, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "distinction", "really", "have", "its", "root", "in", "history"]]}, {"text": "The petition started out; back at the time of Magna Carta petitions only went to the king.", "start": 2374.444, "stop": 2379.936, "duration": 5.49, "cleanText": [["the", "petition", "start", "out", "back", "at", "the", "time", "of", "magna", "carta", "petition", "only", "go", "to", "the", "king"]]}, {"text": "Over time the British government and ultimately the American government developed other mechanisms that were simply more efficient.", "start": 2379.936, "stop": 2389.444, "duration": 9.51, "cleanText": [["over", "time", "the", "british", "government", "and", "ultimately", "the", "american", "government", "develop", "other", "mechanism", "that", "we", "be", "simply", "more", "efficient"]]}, {"text": "So that, for example, at the time the Petition Clause was written, Congress received a large number of petitions from wounded veterans, and after several years of dealing with that it adopted the Invalid Pension Act and turned that over to a somewhat unusual combination of administrative and judicial officials.", "start": 2389.444, "stop": 2411.792, "duration": 22.35, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "for", "example", "at", "the", "time", "the", "petition", "clause", "be", "write", "congress", "receive", "a", "large", "number", "of", "petition", "from", "wounded", "veteran", "and", "after", "several", "year", "of", "deal", "with", "that", "it", "adopt", "the", "invalid", "pension", "act", "and", "turn", "that", "over", "to", "a", "somewhat", "unusual", "combination", "of", "administrative", "and", "judicial", "official"]]}, {"text": "So I think the creation of--", "start": 2411.792, "stop": 2414.426, "duration": 2.63, "cleanText": [["so", "i", "think", "the", "creation", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "What's the earliest English or American case you have that refers to a lawsuit as protected by the Petition Clause?", "start": 2414.426, "stop": 2424.974, "duration": 10.55, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "early", "english", "or", "american", "case", "you", "have", "that", "refers", "to", "a", "lawsuit", "as", "protect", "by", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I'm not familiar with English law in that respect.", "start": 2424.974, "stop": 2432.307, "duration": 7.33, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "familiar", "with", "english", "law", "in", "that", "respect"]]}, {"text": "With regard to the decisions of this Court, I think it's California Motor Transport, which I think is about 40 years ago.", "start": 2432.307, "stop": 2438.514, "duration": 6.21, "cleanText": [["with", "regard", "to", "the", "decision", "of", "this", "court", "i", "think", "it", "be", "california", "motor", "transport", "which", "i", "think", "be", "about", "year", "ago"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "How many?", "start": 2438.514, "stop": 2439.326, "duration": 0.81, "cleanText": [["how", "many"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "About 40.", "start": 2439.326, "stop": 2440.882, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "40 years ago.", "start": 2440.882, "stop": 2442.36, "duration": 1.48, "cleanText": [["year", "ago"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "There's precious little--", "start": 2442.36, "stop": 2444.164, "duration": 1.8, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "precious", "little"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "So for a couple hundred years, nobody -- nobody connected the two?", "start": 2444.164, "stop": 2447.729, "duration": 3.56, "cleanText": [["so", "for", "a", "couple", "hundred", "year", "nobody", "nobody", "connect", "the", "two"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Many of the constitutional issues this Court deals with were not raised for -- for a very long period of time.", "start": 2447.729, "stop": 2455.276, "duration": 7.55, "cleanText": [["many", "of", "the", "constitutional", "issue", "this", "court", "deal", "with", "we", "be", "not", "raise", "for", "for", "a", "very", "long", "period", "of", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the Garcetti case, the district attorney was disciplined for sending a memo because he disagreed with how the trial strategy was supposed to unfold, and then he actually made that argument in court and was disciplined for that.", "start": 2455.276, "stop": 2469.891, "duration": 14.62, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "garcetti", "case", "the", "district", "attorney", "be", "discipline", "for", "send", "a", "memo", "because", "he", "disagree", "with", "how", "the", "trial", "strategy", "be", "suppose", "to", "unfold", "and", "then", "he", "actually", "make", "that", "argument", "in", "court", "and", "be", "discipline", "for", "that"]]}, {"text": "Would he have been protected if he had just gone to court to sue the office of the district attorney on some sort of a prospective injunction saying, with reference to all search warrants you should follow the following procedures?", "start": 2469.891, "stop": 2485.498, "duration": 15.61, "cleanText": [["would", "he", "have", "be", "protect", "if", "he", "have", "just", "go", "to", "court", "to", "sue", "the", "office", "of", "the", "district", "attorney", "on", "some", "sort", "of", "a", "prospective", "injunction", "say", "with", "reference", "to", "all", "search", "warrant", "you", "should", "follow", "the", "following", "procedure"]]}, {"text": "Would that have been protected, even though the memo was not?", "start": 2485.498, "stop": 2487.664, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["would", "that", "have", "be", "protect", "even", "though", "the", "memo", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it would have been a petition.", "start": 2487.664, "stop": 2489.81, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "would", "have", "be", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "It would not necessarily have been protected.", "start": 2489.81, "stop": 2492.177, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "not", "necessarily", "have", "be", "protect"]]}, {"text": "The government has an interest in such matters as an employer, and that might indeed outweigh--", "start": 2492.177, "stop": 2499.226, "duration": 7.05, "cleanText": [["the", "government", "have", "an", "interest", "in", "such", "matter", "as", "an", "employer", "and", "that", "might", "indeed", "outweigh"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you have objected if the same analysis were used in the Petition Clause case as in the actual case?", "start": 2499.226, "stop": 2505.542, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "have", "object", "if", "the", "same", "analysis", "we", "be", "use", "in", "the", "petition", "clause", "case", "as", "in", "the", "actual", "case"]]}, {"text": "Just take the--", "start": 2505.542, "stop": 2507.271, "duration": 1.73, "cleanText": [["just", "take", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Right, right.", "start": 2507.271, "stop": 2507.786, "duration": 0.51, "cleanText": [["right", "right"]]}, {"text": "The question is, was the--", "start": 2507.786, "stop": 2509.327, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "be", "be", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Just white out \"Speech Clause\" and put in \"Petition Clause\" and file the same opinion?", "start": 2509.327, "stop": 2512.732, "duration": 3.4, "cleanText": [["just", "white", "out", "speech", "clause", "and", "put", "in", "petition", "clause", "and", "file", "the", "same", "opinion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The question I take it you're asking is -- is whether the Garcetti principle would apply to a Petition Clause case where the government -- it was part of the official--", "start": 2512.732, "stop": 2525.184, "duration": 12.45, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "i", "take", "it", "you", "be", "ask", "be", "be", "whether", "the", "garcetti", "principle", "would", "apply", "to", "a", "petition", "clause", "case", "where", "the", "government", "it", "be", "part", "of", "the", "official"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "I want to know how the analytic framework differs.", "start": 2525.184, "stop": 2528.484, "duration": 3.3, "cleanText": [["i", "want", "to", "know", "how", "the", "analytic", "framework", "differs"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I don't -- I don't think -- the specific question is whether the Garcetti rule should apply in a Petition Clause case.", "start": 2528.484, "stop": 2543.947, "duration": 15.46, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "i", "do", "not", "think", "the", "specific", "question", "be", "whether", "the", "garcetti", "rule", "should", "apply", "in", "a", "petition", "clause", "case"]]}, {"text": "I don't think we have a position on that.", "start": 2543.947, "stop": 2548.757, "duration": 4.81, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "we", "have", "a", "position", "on", "that"]]}, {"text": "It's not raised in this case.", "start": 2548.757, "stop": 2549.955, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "raise", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Mr. Schnapper, can I ask Justice Kennedy's question in maybe a little bit of a different way?", "start": 2549.955, "stop": 2554.717, "duration": 4.76, "cleanText": [["well", "mr", "schnapper", "can", "i", "ask", "justice", "kennedy", "s", "question", "in", "maybe", "a", "little", "bit", "of", "a", "different", "way"]]}, {"text": "In -- in the Connick inquiry, you have a threshold inquiry and then you have a balancing test.", "start": 2554.717, "stop": 2560.32, "duration": 5.6, "cleanText": [["in", "in", "the", "connick", "inquiry", "you", "have", "a", "threshold", "inquiry", "and", "then", "you", "have", "a", "balance", "test"]]}, {"text": "Now, you're suggesting that the threshold inquiry, the public concern inquiry, is kind of apples and oranges here; it's just not appropriate for the Petition Clause.", "start": 2560.32, "stop": 2569.565, "duration": 9.24, "cleanText": [["now", "you", "be", "suggest", "that", "the", "threshold", "inquiry", "the", "public", "concern", "inquiry", "be", "kind", "of", "apple", "and", "orange", "here", "it", "be", "just", "not", "appropriate", "for", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "But the question that then follows is, should there be a replacement threshold inquiry before you get to the balancing that Connick suggests is the second stage of the process?", "start": 2569.565, "stop": 2581.752, "duration": 12.19, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "question", "that", "then", "follow", "be", "should", "there", "be", "a", "replacement", "threshold", "inquiry", "before", "you", "get", "to", "the", "balancing", "that", "connick", "suggest", "be", "the", "second", "stage", "of", "the", "process"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Probably not in the sense that you're asking.", "start": 2581.752, "stop": 2591.837, "duration": 10.09, "cleanText": [["probably", "not", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "you", "be", "ask"]]}, {"text": "There would be a threshold inquiry as to whether what had happened was petitioning.", "start": 2591.837, "stop": 2597.469, "duration": 5.63, "cleanText": [["there", "would", "be", "a", "threshold", "inquiry", "as", "to", "whether", "what", "have", "happen", "be", "petition"]]}, {"text": "If it were, this Court's decisions indicate that the Court might impose a threshold inquiry consistent with, say, the line of cases, most recently BE&K Construction, as to whether the underlying petition had a -- a reasonable basis or was -- had been pursued in good faith.", "start": 2597.469, "stop": 2620.268, "duration": 22.8, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "we", "be", "this", "court", "s", "decision", "indicate", "that", "the", "court", "might", "impose", "a", "threshold", "inquiry", "consistent", "with", "say", "the", "line", "of", "case", "most", "recently", "be", "k", "construction", "as", "to", "whether", "the", "underlying", "petition", "have", "a", "a", "reasonable", "basis", "or", "be", "have", "be", "pursue", "in", "good", "faith"]]}, {"text": "But I think if you got past that, then there would be no further threshold.", "start": 2620.268, "stop": 2624.301, "duration": 4.03, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "if", "you", "get", "past", "that", "then", "there", "would", "be", "no", "further", "threshold"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if a number of municipal employees prepare a formal document called \"Petition\", and they say: We have a grievance, and our grievance is that the quality of the food in the cafeteria is poor?", "start": 2624.301, "stop": 2635.724, "duration": 11.42, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "a", "number", "of", "municipal", "employee", "prepare", "a", "formal", "document", "call", "petition", "and", "they", "say", "we", "have", "a", "grievance", "and", "our", "grievance", "be", "that", "the", "quality", "of", "the", "food", "in", "the", "cafeteria", "be", "poor"]]}, {"text": "Now, is that protected by the Petition Clause?", "start": 2635.724, "stop": 2639.009, "duration": 3.28, "cleanText": [["now", "be", "that", "protect", "by", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "As you describe it, on our view, not so, because our view is that, putting aside the historical and somewhat unusual but less common instance of a petition directed to, let's say at the Federal level the Congress or the president, the Petition Clause ordinarily applies only where the government has created a specific remedial mechanism for addressing a particular kind of grievance.", "start": 2639.009, "stop": 2666.174, "duration": 27.16, "cleanText": [["as", "you", "describe", "it", "on", "our", "view", "not", "so", "because", "our", "view", "be", "that", "put", "aside", "the", "historical", "and", "somewhat", "unusual", "but", "less", "common", "instance", "of", "a", "petition", "direct", "to", "let", "us", "say", "at", "the", "federal", "level", "the", "congress", "or", "the", "president", "the", "petition", "clause", "ordinarily", "apply", "only", "where", "the", "government", "have", "create", "a", "specific", "remedial", "mechanism", "for", "address", "a", "particular", "kind", "of", "grievance"]]}, {"text": "It's something that's just outside the ordinary give-and-take of the office, something like, you know, a separate agency or an arbitrator or a court, something like that.", "start": 2666.174, "stop": 2674.331, "duration": 8.16, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "something", "that", "be", "just", "outside", "the", "ordinary", "give", "and", "take", "of", "the", "office", "something", "like", "you", "know", "a", "separate", "agency", "or", "an", "arbitrator", "or", "a", "court", "something", "like", "that"]]}, {"text": "And that -- there's an historical--", "start": 2674.331, "stop": 2675.996, "duration": 1.66, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "there", "be", "an", "historical"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Where does that rule come from?", "start": 2675.996, "stop": 2677.178, "duration": 1.18, "cleanText": [["where", "do", "that", "rule", "come", "from"]]}, {"text": "It's drawn out of thin air?", "start": 2677.178, "stop": 2679.855, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "draw", "out", "of", "thin", "air"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No.", "start": 2679.855, "stop": 2680.183, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "No, it isn't.", "start": 2680.183, "stop": 2680.635, "duration": 0.45, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "That's the -- historically, that's the kind of distinction that was there.", "start": 2680.635, "stop": 2684.385, "duration": 3.75, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "historically", "that", "be", "the", "kind", "of", "distinction", "that", "be", "there"]]}, {"text": "If you had a problem in England, if the undersheriff took your cow, you could go to the sheriff, but historically, that wasn't called a petition.", "start": 2684.385, "stop": 2694.218, "duration": 9.83, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "have", "a", "problem", "in", "england", "if", "the", "undersheriff", "take", "your", "cow", "you", "could", "go", "to", "the", "sheriff", "but", "historically", "that", "be", "not", "call", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "If you went to the king, that was a petition.", "start": 2694.218, "stop": 2697.082, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "go", "to", "the", "king", "that", "be", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "It was not going to the local.", "start": 2697.082, "stop": 2699.575, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "go", "to", "the", "local"]]}, {"text": "So we -- we do have a great deal of historical material, as Justice Scalia points out, about individuals, including Federal Government officials, petitioning Congress.", "start": 2699.575, "stop": 2710.264, "duration": 10.69, "cleanText": [["so", "we", "we", "do", "have", "a", "great", "deal", "of", "historical", "material", "as", "justice", "scalia", "point", "out", "about", "individual", "include", "federal", "government", "official", "petition", "congress"]]}, {"text": "And I -- we think the framers would have regarded those as petitions.", "start": 2710.264, "stop": 2713.486, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "we", "think", "the", "framer", "would", "have", "regard", "those", "as", "petition"]]}, {"text": "I don't think they would regard a beef with the Secretary of the Treasury as -- as -- so we would -- there's no--", "start": 2713.486, "stop": 2720.132, "duration": 6.65, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "they", "would", "regard", "a", "beef", "with", "the", "secretary", "of", "the", "treasury", "as", "as", "so", "we", "would", "there", "be", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Schnapper, this is not -- if you're -- if you're talking about the practical significance, Myers in Connick was going around the office, collecting signatures.", "start": 2720.132, "stop": 2733.903, "duration": 13.77, "cleanText": [["mr", "schnapper", "this", "be", "not", "if", "you", "be", "if", "you", "be", "talk", "about", "the", "practical", "significance", "myers", "in", "connick", "be", "go", "around", "the", "office", "collect", "signature"]]}, {"text": "She was taking a poll.", "start": 2733.903, "stop": 2735.648, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["she", "be", "take", "a", "poll"]]}, {"text": "She was taking a poll and the poll was going to be presented to the employer.", "start": 2735.648, "stop": 2740.876, "duration": 5.23, "cleanText": [["she", "be", "take", "a", "poll", "and", "the", "poll", "be", "go", "to", "be", "present", "to", "the", "employer"]]}, {"text": "That sounds much more petition-like than filing a grievance pursuant to a collective bargaining agreement.", "start": 2740.876, "stop": 2748.409, "duration": 7.53, "cleanText": [["that", "sound", "much", "more", "petition", "like", "than", "file", "a", "grievance", "pursuant", "to", "a", "collective", "bargaining", "agreement"]]}, {"text": "So the -- the distinction between Connick, who was taking a poll -- why wasn't that a petition?", "start": 2748.409, "stop": 2762.636, "duration": 14.23, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "the", "distinction", "between", "connick", "who", "be", "take", "a", "poll", "why", "be", "not", "that", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "Maybe -- did she just put the wrong label on it?", "start": 2762.636, "stop": 2766.166, "duration": 3.53, "cleanText": [["maybe", "do", "she", "just", "put", "the", "wrong", "label", "on", "it"]]}, {"text": "If she called her case a petition case, it would have been all right?", "start": 2766.166, "stop": 2770.23, "duration": 4.06, "cleanText": [["if", "she", "call", "her", "case", "a", "petition", "case", "it", "would", "have", "be", "all", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No.", "start": 2770.23, "stop": 2770.355, "duration": 0.13, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "No, Your Honor.", "start": 2770.355, "stop": 2770.992, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Our view, as I indicated to Justice Alito, is that a gripe within the office, whether you label it a petition or not, would not, except in maybe some extraordinary circumstance, constitute a petition.", "start": 2770.992, "stop": 2784.985, "duration": 13.99, "cleanText": [["our", "view", "as", "i", "indicate", "to", "justice", "alito", "be", "that", "a", "gripe", "within", "the", "office", "whether", "you", "label", "it", "a", "petition", "or", "not", "would", "not", "except", "in", "maybe", "some", "extraordinary", "circumstance", "constitute", "a", "petition"]]}, {"text": "But if I might respond, I think your question raises a second important linguistic point, which is the word 18th century.", "start": 2784.985, "stop": 2796.625, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "i", "might", "respond", "i", "think", "your", "question", "raise", "a", "second", "important", "linguistic", "point", "which", "be", "the", "word", "th", "century"]]}, {"text": "We think of petitions as the things you see out on tables, along the street; people say, come on, sign my petition to do this, that, or the other thing.", "start": 2796.625, "stop": 2804.268, "duration": 7.64, "cleanText": [["we", "think", "of", "petition", "as", "the", "thing", "you", "see", "out", "on", "table", "along", "the", "street", "people", "say", "come", "on", "sign", "my", "petition", "to", "do", "this", "that", "or", "the", "other", "thing"]]}, {"text": "That was not a common phenomena in the 18th century.", "start": 2804.268, "stop": 2807.922, "duration": 3.65, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "a", "common", "phenomenon", "in", "the", "th", "century"]]}, {"text": "Petitions were ordinarily things from one individual or a couple of people.", "start": 2807.922, "stop": 2811.859, "duration": 3.94, "cleanText": [["petition", "we", "be", "ordinarily", "thing", "from", "one", "individual", "or", "a", "couple", "of", "people"]]}, {"text": "There were some exceptions, but that was -- that was not the normal -- the normal practice.", "start": 2811.859, "stop": 2816.264, "duration": 4.41, "cleanText": [["there", "we", "be", "some", "exception", "but", "that", "be", "that", "be", "not", "the", "normal", "the", "normal", "practice"]]}, {"text": "In fact, the very idea that you could have large numbers of people signing something called a petition was much controverted at that time.", "start": 2816.264, "stop": 2825.4, "duration": 9.14, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "the", "very", "idea", "that", "you", "could", "have", "large", "number", "of", "people", "sign", "something", "call", "a", "petition", "be", "much", "controvert", "at", "that", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, you're the expert in this area, but that -- that surprises me.", "start": 2825.4, "stop": 2829.758, "duration": 4.36, "cleanText": [["well", "you", "be", "the", "expert", "in", "this", "area", "but", "that", "that", "surprise", "me"]]}, {"text": "I thought it was quite common in the early 1800s for you to go to all your neighbors -- and the book \"Quarreling About Slavery\" explains this, where there were petitions signed by many of the constituents in the congressman's district.", "start": 2829.758, "stop": 2847.796, "duration": 18.04, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "quite", "common", "in", "the", "early", "s", "for", "you", "to", "go", "to", "all", "your", "neighbor", "and", "the", "book", "quarrel", "about", "slavery", "explain", "this", "where", "there", "we", "be", "petition", "sign", "by", "many", "of", "the", "constituent", "in", "the", "congressman", "s", "district"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "There -- there were.", "start": 2847.796, "stop": 2849.462, "duration": 1.67, "cleanText": [["there", "there", "we", "be"]]}, {"text": "It came to be used that way as -- that is largely a--", "start": 2849.462, "stop": 2851.731, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["it", "come", "to", "be", "use", "that", "way", "as", "that", "be", "largely", "a"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And there were scores, scores of -- of signatures on these petitions.", "start": 2851.731, "stop": 2855.45, "duration": 3.72, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "we", "be", "score", "score", "of", "of", "signature", "on", "these", "petition"]]}, {"text": "So that's like your card table.", "start": 2855.45, "stop": 2856.838, "duration": 1.39, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "be", "like", "your", "card", "table"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It is, but what I'm suggesting is that is a 19th and 20th-century phenomenon.", "start": 2856.838, "stop": 2861.832, "duration": 4.99, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "but", "what", "I", "be", "suggest", "be", "that", "be", "a", "th", "and", "th", "century", "phenomenon"]]}, {"text": "You see very little of that in the 18th century or earlier.", "start": 2861.832, "stop": 2864.679, "duration": 2.85, "cleanText": [["you", "see", "very", "little", "of", "that", "in", "the", "th", "century", "or", "early"]]}, {"text": "And I'd note, although -- I mean, I, I think that if that's done by private individuals and directed to the government, it would be protected by the Petition Clause.", "start": 2864.679, "stop": 2873.302, "duration": 8.62, "cleanText": [["and", "I", "would", "note", "although", "i", "mean", "i", "i", "think", "that", "if", "that", "be", "do", "by", "private", "individual", "and", "direct", "to", "the", "government", "it", "would", "be", "protect", "by", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "I note, just to give you a sense of the history, that at the time that happened, its legitimacy was challenged, and the argument was made by the proponents of slavery in support of a gag order adopted by Congress that this was not really a legitimate petition.", "start": 2873.302, "stop": 2888.226, "duration": 14.92, "cleanText": [["i", "note", "just", "to", "give", "you", "a", "sense", "of", "the", "history", "that", "at", "the", "time", "that", "happen", "its", "legitimacy", "be", "challenge", "and", "the", "argument", "be", "make", "by", "the", "proponent", "of", "slavery", "in", "support", "of", "a", "gag", "order", "adopt", "by", "congress", "that", "this", "be", "not", "really", "a", "legitimate", "petition"]]}, {"text": "The legitimate petition ought to be something about your personal problems; an abolitionist really had no business signing these things; it wasn't a personal grievance.", "start": 2888.226, "stop": 2897.409, "duration": 9.18, "cleanText": [["the", "legitimate", "petition", "ought", "to", "be", "something", "about", "your", "personal", "problem", "an", "abolitionist", "really", "have", "no", "business", "sign", "these", "thing", "it", "be", "not", "a", "personal", "grievance"]]}, {"text": "Now, I think that's wrong.", "start": 2897.409, "stop": 2899.961, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think", "that", "be", "wrong"]]}, {"text": "I think it's certainly not consistent with current case law.", "start": 2899.961, "stop": 2902.388, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "it", "be", "certainly", "not", "consistent", "with", "current", "case", "law"]]}, {"text": "But it illustrates how the position advanced by Petitioners stands on its head the historical evolution of the Petition Clause, which starts as about private matters, and only over time and after a good deal of struggle is it extended to things of broader concern and possibly a petition signed by people who don't have a personal stake in--", "start": 2902.388, "stop": 2922.185, "duration": 19.8, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "illustrate", "how", "the", "position", "advance", "by", "petitioner", "stand", "on", "its", "head", "the", "historical", "evolution", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "which", "start", "as", "about", "private", "matter", "and", "only", "over", "time", "and", "after", "a", "good", "deal", "of", "struggle", "be", "it", "extend", "to", "thing", "of", "broad", "concern", "and", "possibly", "a", "petition", "sign", "by", "people", "who", "do", "not", "have", "a", "personal", "stake", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was the Calhoun position, not the John Q. Adams position.", "start": 2922.185, "stop": 2924.861, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "calhoun", "position", "not", "the", "john", "q", "adams", "position"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Right.", "start": 2924.861, "stop": 2926.075, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "Right.", "start": 2926.075, "stop": 2926.808, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "That's right.", "start": 2926.808, "stop": 2927.444, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Schnapper, let's come to the century in which we are now living.", "start": 2927.444, "stop": 2935.898, "duration": 8.45, "cleanText": [["mr", "schnapper", "let", "us", "come", "to", "the", "century", "in", "which", "we", "be", "now", "live"]]}, {"text": "We have Title VII.", "start": 2935.898, "stop": 2938.511, "duration": 2.61, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "title", "vii"]]}, {"text": "Title VII has this provision, an explicit provision against retaliation.", "start": 2938.511, "stop": 2945.015, "duration": 6.5, "cleanText": [["title", "vii", "have", "this", "provision", "an", "explicit", "provision", "against", "retaliation"]]}, {"text": "But suppose it didn't.", "start": 2945.015, "stop": 2947.553, "duration": 2.54, "cleanText": [["but", "suppose", "it", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "Suppose it just prohibited discrimination and it didn't have a retaliation clause.", "start": 2947.553, "stop": 2954.774, "duration": 7.22, "cleanText": [["suppose", "it", "just", "prohibit", "discrimination", "and", "it", "do", "not", "have", "a", "retaliation", "clause"]]}, {"text": "It's the thrust of your arguments that the government employee would have a claim for retaliation, although someone in the private sector would not?", "start": 2954.774, "stop": 2968.764, "duration": 13.99, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "thrust", "of", "your", "argument", "that", "the", "government", "employee", "would", "have", "a", "claim", "for", "retaliation", "although", "someone", "in", "the", "private", "sector", "would", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Exactly.", "start": 2968.764, "stop": 2969.279, "duration": 0.51, "cleanText": [["exactly"]]}, {"text": "And here we part company with -- I think the government expressed the concern in its brief and perhaps at oral argument -- I guess it was Petitioner that made this point -- that there was something amiss about government employees having rights that private employees don't.", "start": 2969.279, "stop": 2983.752, "duration": 14.47, "cleanText": [["and", "here", "we", "part", "company", "with", "i", "think", "the", "government", "express", "the", "concern", "in", "its", "brief", "and", "perhaps", "at", "oral", "argument", "i", "guess", "it", "be", "petitioner", "that", "make", "this", "point", "that", "there", "be", "something", "amiss", "about", "government", "employee", "have", "right", "that", "private", "employee", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "That distinction exists because the Bill of Rights and the -- and the other constitutional guarantees, with the exception of the Thirteenth Amendment and the right to travel in interstate commerce, those rights don't apply to private -- to people dealing with private employers.", "start": 2983.752, "stop": 2999.126, "duration": 15.37, "cleanText": [["that", "distinction", "exist", "because", "the", "bill", "of", "right", "and", "the", "and", "the", "other", "constitutional", "guarantee", "with", "the", "exception", "of", "the", "thirteenth", "amendment", "and", "the", "right", "to", "travel", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "those", "right", "do", "not", "apply", "to", "private", "to", "people", "deal", "with", "private", "employer"]]}, {"text": "That's just--", "start": 2999.126, "stop": 2999.251, "duration": 0.13, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "just"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "But -- but that's the basis of our law in this area is that when the government is actually the employer the rights of the individuals are somewhat different, and they're closer to the rights that private employees have.", "start": 2999.251, "stop": 3012.512, "duration": 13.26, "cleanText": [["but", "but", "that", "be", "the", "basis", "of", "our", "law", "in", "this", "area", "be", "that", "when", "the", "government", "be", "actually", "the", "employer", "the", "right", "of", "the", "individual", "be", "somewhat", "different", "and", "they", "be", "closer", "to", "the", "right", "that", "private", "employee", "have"]]}, {"text": "So simply saying that these constitutional provisions apply against the government and therefore, you don't have to worry about the distinction between private employers and government employers doesn't seem to be -- me to be completely responsive to our precedent.", "start": 3012.512, "stop": 3026.831, "duration": 14.32, "cleanText": [["so", "simply", "say", "that", "these", "constitutional", "provision", "apply", "against", "the", "government", "and", "therefore", "you", "do", "not", "have", "to", "worry", "about", "the", "distinction", "between", "private", "employer", "and", "government", "employer", "do", "not", "seem", "to", "be", "me", "to", "be", "completely", "responsive", "to", "our", "precedent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And -- and we're not taking issue with the assertion of the government that the government as an employer has interests which are different than it -- it -- those it has just as a sovereign.", "start": 3026.831, "stop": 3038.765, "duration": 11.93, "cleanText": [["and", "and", "we", "be", "not", "take", "issue", "with", "the", "assertion", "of", "the", "government", "that", "the", "government", "as", "an", "employer", "have", "interest", "which", "be", "different", "than", "it", "it", "those", "it", "have", "just", "as", "a", "sovereign"]]}, {"text": "But that distinction has nothing to do with the distinction they propose in this case between matters of public concern and matters of only private concern.", "start": 3038.765, "stop": 3046.719, "duration": 7.95, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "distinction", "have", "nothing", "to", "do", "with", "the", "distinction", "they", "propose", "in", "this", "case", "between", "matter", "of", "public", "concern", "and", "matter", "of", "only", "private", "concern"]]}, {"text": "Indeed, to the contrary.", "start": 3046.719, "stop": 3048.041, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["indeed", "to", "the", "contrary"]]}, {"text": "To the extent that the government's -- the government's interests might be greater, surely a petition that deals with a matter of public importance is going to cause the government a lot more trouble than a purely private matter.", "start": 3048.041, "stop": 3062.327, "duration": 14.29, "cleanText": [["to", "the", "extent", "that", "the", "government", "s", "the", "government", "s", "interest", "might", "be", "great", "surely", "a", "petition", "that", "deal", "with", "a", "matter", "of", "public", "importance", "be", "go", "to", "because", "the", "government", "a", "lot", "more", "trouble", "than", "a", "purely", "private", "matter"]]}, {"text": "A lawsuit alleging systemic employment discrimination on the basis of religion or even an individual, if -- if Mr. Guarnieri had alleged and a court had found that he had been fired because he was Catholic, the ramifications politically and in terms of just -- the ramifications in terms of the workplace would have been far more serious than the--", "start": 3062.327, "stop": 3086.452, "duration": 24.13, "cleanText": [["a", "lawsuit", "allege", "systemic", "employment", "discrimination", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "religion", "or", "even", "an", "individual", "if", "if", "mr", "guarnieri", "have", "allege", "and", "a", "court", "have", "find", "that", "he", "have", "be", "fire", "because", "he", "be", "catholic", "the", "ramification", "politically", "and", "in", "term", "of", "just", "the", "ramification", "in", "term", "of", "the", "workplace", "would", "have", "be", "far", "more", "serious", "than", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Schnapper, isn't the real question in these cases whether the employee is acting as a citizen or instead whether the employee is acting as an employee?", "start": 3086.452, "stop": 3096.161, "duration": 9.71, "cleanText": [["mr", "schnapper", "be", "not", "the", "real", "question", "in", "these", "case", "whether", "the", "employee", "be", "act", "as", "a", "citizen", "or", "instead", "whether", "the", "employee", "be", "act", "as", "an", "employee"]]}, {"text": "And in the speech cases, that distinction suggests a public concern threshold inquiry.", "start": 3096.161, "stop": 3103.367, "duration": 7.21, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "the", "speech", "case", "that", "distinction", "suggest", "a", "public", "concern", "threshold", "inquiry"]]}, {"text": "Maybe in the petition cases it suggests something else, but that that's really the question we should be asking is, is this employee acting as an employee or as a citizen?", "start": 3103.367, "stop": 3112.862, "duration": 9.49, "cleanText": [["maybe", "in", "the", "petition", "case", "it", "suggest", "something", "else", "but", "that", "that", "be", "really", "the", "question", "we", "should", "be", "ask", "be", "be", "this", "employee", "act", "as", "an", "employee", "or", "as", "a", "citizen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--With all due respect, our view is it depends whether or not the -- the employee is acting as a petitioner within the meaning of the Petition Clause.", "start": 3112.862, "stop": 3119.728, "duration": 6.87, "cleanText": [["with", "all", "due", "respect", "our", "view", "be", "it", "depend", "whether", "or", "not", "the", "the", "employee", "be", "act", "as", "a", "petitioner", "within", "the", "meaning", "of", "the", "petition", "clause"]]}, {"text": "The petition Clause was not adopted, like the Free Speech Clause, to foster a vigorous public debate.", "start": 3119.728, "stop": 3125.641, "duration": 5.91, "cleanText": [["the", "petition", "clause", "be", "not", "adopt", "like", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "to", "foster", "a", "vigorous", "public", "debate"]]}, {"text": "The purpose of the Petition Clause, as the Court said in Christopher v. Harbury, is to enable an individual to seek relief for a wrong.", "start": 3125.641, "stop": 3136.38, "duration": 10.74, "cleanText": [["the", "purpose", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "as", "the", "court", "say", "in", "christopher", "v", "harbury", "be", "to", "enable", "an", "individual", "to", "seek", "relief", "for", "a", "wrong"]]}, {"text": "And that has -- that's not the same as the -- the free speech interests that -- that might exist to engage as a citizen in a robust public debate.", "start": 3136.38, "stop": 3147.055, "duration": 10.67, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "have", "that", "be", "not", "the", "same", "as", "the", "the", "free", "speech", "interest", "that", "that", "might", "exist", "to", "engage", "as", "a", "citizen", "in", "a", "robust", "public", "debate"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Guarnieri didn't file his complaint in Federal court, for example, looking to the second petition, in the hopes of a robust debate between himself and Judge Caputo.", "start": 3147.055, "stop": 3156.549, "duration": 9.49, "cleanText": [["mr", "guarnieri", "do", "not", "file", "his", "complaint", "in", "federal", "court", "for", "example", "look", "to", "the", "second", "petition", "in", "the", "hope", "of", "a", "robust", "debate", "between", "himself", "and", "judge", "caputo"]]}, {"text": "He -- he filed that complaint to get redress for an alleged violation of his constitutional rights.", "start": 3156.549, "stop": 3164.036, "duration": 7.49, "cleanText": [["he", "he", "file", "that", "complaint", "to", "get", "redress", "for", "an", "alleged", "violation", "of", "his", "constitutional", "right"]]}, {"text": "So -- so the citizen versus employee distinction in -- in Connick is inapt here.", "start": 3164.036, "stop": 3171.783, "duration": 7.75, "cleanText": [["so", "so", "the", "citizen", "versus", "employee", "distinction", "in", "in", "connick", "be", "inapt", "here"]]}, {"text": "It's -- it's -- it's rooted in the purpose of the -- of the Free Speech Clause, which is protecting vigorous public debate on matters of public concern.", "start": 3171.783, "stop": 3180.997, "duration": 9.21, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "it", "be", "it", "be", "root", "in", "the", "purpose", "of", "the", "of", "the", "free", "speech", "clause", "which", "be", "protect", "vigorous", "public", "debate", "on", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}, {"text": "The Petition Clause is not about matters of public concern.", "start": 3180.997, "stop": 3185.09, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["the", "petition", "clause", "be", "not", "about", "matter", "of", "public", "concern"]]}, {"text": "It's about -- about people's ability to seek redress.", "start": 3185.09, "stop": 3189.463, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "about", "about", "people", "s", "ability", "to", "seek", "redress"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't guarantee redress, but it protects the ability to ask for it.", "start": 3189.463, "stop": 3192.779, "duration": 3.32, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "guarantee", "redress", "but", "it", "protect", "the", "ability", "to", "ask", "for", "it"]]}, {"text": "The--", "start": 3192.779, "stop": 3195.132, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "You do, I think, recognize that it would be possible then to circumvent Connick if you could turn around and file a pleading and say: Now I have a petition, not just a grievance.", "start": 3195.132, "stop": 3211.816, "duration": 16.68, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "i", "think", "recognize", "that", "it", "would", "be", "possible", "then", "to", "circumvent", "connick", "if", "you", "could", "turn", "around", "and", "file", "a", "pleading", "and", "say", "now", "i", "have", "a", "petition", "not", "just", "a", "grievance"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, we don't think that that is a serious problem for three reasons.", "start": 3211.816, "stop": 3217.991, "duration": 6.18, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "we", "do", "not", "think", "that", "that", "be", "a", "serious", "problem", "for", "three", "reason"]]}, {"text": "First of all, the Petitioners have in -- in highly expressive language described the decision in Filippo as one which would lead to an avalanche, tsunami, an overwhelming number of new lawsuits.", "start": 3217.991, "stop": 3233.431, "duration": 15.44, "cleanText": [["first", "of", "all", "the", "petitioner", "have", "in", "in", "highly", "expressive", "language", "describe", "the", "decision", "in", "filippo", "as", "one", "which", "would", "lead", "to", "an", "avalanche", "tsunami", "an", "overwhelming", "number", "of", "new", "lawsuit"]]}, {"text": "We pointed out in our reply brief that they had not adduced any evidence that any such thing had happened in the 17 years since San Filippo.", "start": 3233.431, "stop": 3242.069, "duration": 8.64, "cleanText": [["we", "point", "out", "in", "our", "reply", "brief", "that", "they", "have", "not", "adduce", "any", "evidence", "that", "any", "such", "thing", "have", "happen", "in", "the", "year", "since", "san", "filippo"]]}, {"text": "Their reply brief does not purport to have any information to -- to support that.", "start": 3242.069, "stop": 3248.744, "duration": 6.68, "cleanText": [["their", "reply", "brief", "do", "not", "purport", "to", "have", "any", "information", "to", "to", "support", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but things will be a lot different if we give the sanction to your theory.", "start": 3248.744, "stop": 3252.621, "duration": 3.88, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "thing", "will", "be", "a", "lot", "different", "if", "we", "give", "the", "sanction", "to", "your", "theory"]]}, {"text": "I think the idea that it hasn't happened in 17 years in the wake of San Filippo is a little bit -- it's not very compelling.", "start": 3252.621, "stop": 3260.155, "duration": 7.53, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "idea", "that", "it", "have", "not", "happen", "in", "year", "in", "the", "wake", "of", "san", "filippo", "be", "a", "little", "bit", "it", "be", "not", "very", "compelling"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think your -- I think there are two -- two other reasons why this is not a -- a major concern.", "start": 3260.155, "stop": 3265.007, "duration": 4.85, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "your", "i", "think", "there", "be", "two", "two", "other", "reason", "why", "this", "be", "not", "a", "a", "major", "concern"]]}, {"text": "The first one is it simply isn't the case that you could take any beef, write \"Federal complaint\" at the top of it and file it in Federal court and be protected.", "start": 3265.007, "stop": 3275.95, "duration": 10.94, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "one", "be", "it", "simply", "be", "not", "the", "case", "that", "you", "could", "take", "any", "beef", "write", "federal", "complaint", "at", "the", "top", "of", "it", "and", "file", "it", "in", "federal", "court", "and", "be", "protect"]]}, {"text": "Most internal gripes don't raise a colorable claim under Federal or State law, and this Court's Petition Clause cases make it clear that a petition, particularly a lawsuit, that doesn't have a reasonable basis simply isn't going to be protected.", "start": 3275.95, "stop": 3292.365, "duration": 16.41, "cleanText": [["most", "internal", "gripe", "do", "not", "raise", "a", "colorable", "claim", "under", "federal", "or", "state", "law", "and", "this", "court", "s", "petition", "clause", "case", "make", "it", "clear", "that", "a", "petition", "particularly", "a", "lawsuit", "that", "do", "not", "have", "a", "reasonable", "basis", "simply", "be", "not", "go", "to", "be", "protect"]]}, {"text": "It's also, to be frank, based on my contact with private petitioners, it's highly unrealistic to suggest that if an employee, government employee, took some gripe and went to a lawyer and said, let's file this in Federal court, I want to get it off my chest, to find a lawyer on a contingent fee basis that is going to do that.", "start": 3292.365, "stop": 3311.804, "duration": 19.44, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "also", "to", "be", "frank", "base", "on", "my", "contact", "with", "private", "petitioner", "it", "be", "highly", "unrealistic", "to", "suggest", "that", "if", "an", "employee", "government", "employee", "take", "some", "gripe", "and", "go", "to", "a", "lawyer", "and", "say", "let", "us", "file", "this", "in", "federal", "court", "i", "want", "to", "get", "it", "off", "my", "chest", "to", "find", "a", "lawyer", "on", "a", "contingent", "fee", "basis", "that", "be", "go", "to", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "If a chance case has no chance of success, you're not going to find a lawyer who will do it; and on a police officer's salary, you're certainly not going to be able to hire one.", "start": 3311.804, "stop": 3318.81, "duration": 7.01, "cleanText": [["if", "a", "chance", "case", "have", "no", "chance", "of", "success", "you", "be", "not", "go", "to", "find", "a", "lawyer", "who", "will", "do", "it", "and", "on", "a", "police", "officer", "s", "salary", "you", "be", "certainly", "not", "go", "to", "be", "able", "to", "hire", "one"]]}, {"text": "Third--", "start": 3318.81, "stop": 3320.241, "duration": 1.43, "cleanText": [["third"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but the most likely solution when you have an employee grievance along with it is that some umbrella settlement -- I mean, the employer doesn't want to spend -- I mean, that's part of the reason our doctrine developed under the First Amendment.", "start": 3320.241, "stop": 3331.914, "duration": 11.67, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "the", "most", "likely", "solution", "when", "you", "have", "an", "employee", "grievance", "along", "with", "it", "be", "that", "some", "umbrella", "settlement", "i", "mean", "the", "employer", "do", "not", "want", "to", "spend", "i", "mean", "that", "be", "part", "of", "the", "reason", "our", "doctrine", "develop", "under", "the", "first", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "The employer doesn't want to have to worry about spending time and money in court to resolve what is essentially an employee grievance.", "start": 3331.914, "stop": 3340.629, "duration": 8.71, "cleanText": [["the", "employer", "do", "not", "want", "to", "have", "to", "worry", "about", "spending", "time", "and", "money", "in", "court", "to", "resolve", "what", "be", "essentially", "an", "employee", "grievance"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Few -- few private lawyers who aren't independently wealthy are going to take a baseless case on the theory that they're going to get some umbrella settlement.", "start": 3340.629, "stop": 3348.084, "duration": 7.45, "cleanText": [["few", "few", "private", "lawyer", "who", "be", "not", "independently", "wealthy", "be", "go", "to", "take", "a", "baseless", "case", "on", "the", "theory", "that", "they", "be", "go", "to", "get", "some", "umbrella", "settlement"]]}, {"text": "It's just -- it simply doesn't happen.", "start": 3348.084, "stop": 3350.015, "duration": 1.93, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "just", "it", "simply", "do", "not", "happen"]]}, {"text": "It -- it -- and realistically, we don't really have a plausible account of why an employee would do this.", "start": 3350.015, "stop": 3357.201, "duration": 7.19, "cleanText": [["it", "it", "and", "realistically", "we", "do", "not", "really", "have", "a", "plausible", "account", "of", "why", "an", "employee", "would", "do", "this"]]}, {"text": "I mean, you're an employee, you're unhappy with the way you're being treated at work, you--", "start": 3357.201, "stop": 3361.25, "duration": 4.05, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "you", "be", "an", "employee", "you", "be", "unhappy", "with", "the", "way", "you", "be", "be", "treat", "at", "work", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counselor, your client won everything in his collective bargaining grievance.", "start": 3361.25, "stop": 3367.444, "duration": 6.19, "cleanText": [["counselor", "your", "client", "win", "everything", "in", "his", "collective", "bargaining", "grievance"]]}, {"text": "He got his pay back, he got them to stop doing what they did, and he found a lawyer to file a constitutional claim.", "start": 3367.444, "stop": 3374.541, "duration": 7.1, "cleanText": [["he", "get", "his", "pay", "back", "he", "get", "them", "to", "stop", "do", "what", "they", "do", "and", "he", "find", "a", "lawyer", "to", "file", "a", "constitutional", "claim"]]}, {"text": "So your suggestion that lawyers won't fight semi-chaotic adventures is realistic as well.", "start": 3374.541, "stop": 3385.105, "duration": 10.56, "cleanText": [["so", "your", "suggestion", "that", "lawyer", "will", "not", "fight", "semi", "chaotic", "adventure", "be", "realistic", "as", "well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, this--", "start": 3385.105, "stop": 3386.291, "duration": 1.19, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "this"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "People get upset about how they're treated all of the time, and they find lawyers to file suits about that treatment.", "start": 3386.291, "stop": 3393.883, "duration": 7.59, "cleanText": [["people", "get", "upset", "about", "how", "they", "be", "treat", "all", "of", "the", "time", "and", "they", "find", "lawyer", "to", "file", "suit", "about", "that", "treatment"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Your Honor, I can certainly tell you that people who are upset all the time call me ostensibly unable to find lawyers.", "start": 3393.883, "stop": 3399.984, "duration": 6.1, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "i", "can", "certainly", "tell", "you", "that", "people", "who", "be", "upset", "all", "the", "time", "call", "me", "ostensibly", "unable", "to", "find", "lawyer"]]}, {"text": "I mean, remember, the -- the fact that Mr. Guarnieri was able to find a lawyer to take this case doesn't prove that people can find lawyers to take baseless cases.", "start": 3399.984, "stop": 3408.559, "duration": 8.58, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "remember", "the", "the", "fact", "that", "mr", "guarnieri", "be", "able", "to", "find", "a", "lawyer", "to", "take", "this", "case", "do", "not", "prove", "that", "people", "can", "find", "lawyer", "to", "take", "baseless", "case"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Guarnieri found a lawyer, she brought this case, she got past summary judgment, she took it to trial and she won.", "start": 3408.559, "stop": 3415.564, "duration": 7, "cleanText": [["mr", "guarnieri", "find", "a", "lawyer", "she", "bring", "this", "case", "she", "get", "past", "summary", "judgment", "she", "take", "it", "to", "trial", "and", "she", "win"]]}, {"text": "This is a case that not only had a substantial basis, but on the facts, and this issue is no longer before us, she prevailed.", "start": 3415.564, "stop": 3421.585, "duration": 6.02, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "a", "case", "that", "not", "only", "have", "a", "substantial", "basis", "but", "on", "the", "fact", "and", "this", "issue", "be", "no", "longer", "before", "us", "she", "prevail"]]}, {"text": "If the Court has no--", "start": 3421.585, "stop": 3424.822, "duration": 3.24, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "court", "have", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your submission is there are not very many -- throughout the whole country there are very few frivolous 1983 cases or employment cases, that's your point?", "start": 3424.822, "stop": 3435.562, "duration": 10.74, "cleanText": [["your", "submission", "be", "there", "be", "not", "very", "many", "throughout", "the", "whole", "country", "there", "be", "very", "few", "frivolous", "case", "or", "employment", "case", "that", "be", "your", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Eric Schnapper", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, they -- they -- certainly they happen, but the notion that this is going to unleash a flood of them seems to me unrealistic.", "start": 3435.562, "stop": 3442.704, "duration": 7.14, "cleanText": [["no", "they", "they", "certainly", "they", "happen", "but", "the", "notion", "that", "this", "be", "go", "to", "unleash", "a", "flood", "of", "them", "seem", "to", "me", "unrealistic"]]}, {"text": "A particular institution like this where the theory of this is that the private -- the government employee reads Connick, realizes they can't write a letter to the boss with -- with their gripe, and undissatisfied with their ability to talk about it with friends and family and gripe with pals at the bar, decides that the only way they can get it off their chest is to have it be in a complaint in some Federal courthouse, where it would then probably be dismissed.", "start": 3442.704, "stop": 3469.864, "duration": 27.16, "cleanText": [["a", "particular", "institution", "like", "this", "where", "the", "theory", "of", "this", "be", "that", "the", "private", "the", "government", "employee", "read", "connick", "realize", "they", "can", "not", "write", "a", "letter", "to", "the", "bos", "with", "with", "their", "gripe", "and", "undissatisfied", "with", "their", "ability", "to", "talk", "about", "it", "with", "friend", "and", "family", "and", "gripe", "with", "pal", "at", "the", "bar", "decide", "that", "the", "only", "way", "they", "can", "get", "it", "off", "their", "chest", "be", "to", "have", "it", "be", "in", "a", "complaint", "in", "some", "federal", "courthouse", "where", "it", "would", "then", "probably", "be", "dismiss"]]}, {"text": "I think in the real world that's something that would make very little sense to an employee.", "start": 3469.864, "stop": 3475.73, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "in", "the", "real", "world", "that", "be", "something", "that", "would", "make", "very", "little", "sense", "to", "an", "employee"]]}, {"text": "If the Court has no further questions--", "start": 3475.73, "stop": 3477.643, "duration": 1.91, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "court", "have", "no", "further", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, counsel.", "start": 3477.643, "stop": 3479.324, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "counsel"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Palmore, you have a minute left.", "start": 3479.324, "stop": 3481.598, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["mr", "palmore", "you", "have", "a", "minute", "left"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Joseph R. Palmore", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, it defies the imagination that the radical Republicans and the framers understood that the Petition Clause would constitutionalize public employee grievance, and as academic commentary that Respondent cites suggests, their -- Respondents long-centered view of the Petition Clause would call into question, sovereign immunity doctrine, parts of Rule 11, suggest a right to appeal and a right to judicial review whenever anyone has agreed to government action.", "start": 3481.598, "stop": 3506.76, "duration": 25.16, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "it", "defy", "the", "imagination", "that", "the", "radical", "republican", "and", "the", "framer", "understand", "that", "the", "petition", "clause", "would", "constitutionalize", "public", "employee", "grievance", "and", "as", "academic", "commentary", "that", "respondent", "cite", "suggests", "their", "respondent", "long", "center", "view", "of", "the", "petition", "clause", "would", "call", "into", "question", "sovereign", "immunity", "doctrine", "part", "of", "rule", "suggest", "a", "right", "to", "appeal", "and", "a", "right", "to", "judicial", "review", "whenever", "anyone", "have", "agree", "to", "government", "action"]]}, {"text": "There is also a danger that it would constitutionalize the arbitration process whenever the government is a party.", "start": 3506.76, "stop": 3512.706, "duration": 5.95, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "also", "a", "danger", "that", "it", "would", "constitutionalize", "the", "arbitration", "process", "whenever", "the", "government", "be", "a", "party"]]}, {"text": "If I can just answer one question.", "start": 3512.706, "stop": 3515.74, "duration": 3.03, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "can", "just", "answer", "one", "question"]]}, {"text": "Connick is focused not on where speech happens, as Respondent insists, but rather where its effects occur.", "start": 3515.74, "stop": 3522.899, "duration": 7.16, "cleanText": [["connick", "be", "focus", "not", "on", "where", "speech", "happen", "as", "respondent", "insists", "but", "rather", "where", "its", "effect", "occur"]]}, {"text": "As this Court held in the City of San Diego v. Roe, employee speech completely outside of the workplace raises the same kind of concerns.", "start": 3522.899, "stop": 3534.383, "duration": 11.48, "cleanText": [["as", "this", "court", "hold", "in", "the", "city", "of", "san", "diego", "v", "roe", "employee", "speech", "completely", "outside", "of", "the", "workplace", "raise", "the", "same", "kind", "of", "concern"]]}, {"text": "If there are no further questions, Petitioners will rest on their submissions.", "start": 3534.383, "stop": 3537.653, "duration": 3.27, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "no", "further", "question", "petitioner", "will", "rest", "on", "their", "submission"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, counsel.", "start": 3537.653, "stop": 3539.661, "duration": 2.01, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "counsel"]]}, {"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 3539.661, "stop": 3540.703, "duration": 1.04, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Roberts Court", "arguedOn": "Mar 22, 2011", "petitioner": "Borough of Duryea, Pennsylvania, et al.", "respondent": "harles J. Guarnieri", "docket": "09-1476", "citation": "564US_(2011)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/564/09-1476", "lowerCourt": "United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit", "grantedOn": "Oct 12, 2010", "decidedOn": "Jun 20, 2011", "wikiData": {"title": "Borough of Duryea v. Guarnieri", "Litigants": "Borough of Duryea v. Guarnieri", "ArgueDate": "March 22", "ArgueYear": "2011", "DecideDate": "June 20", "DecideYear": "2011", "FullName": "Borough of Duryea, Pennsylvania, et al., Petitioners v. Charles J. Guarnieri", "Docket": "09-1476", "USVol": "564", "USPage": "379", "ParallelCitations": "131 S. Ct. 2488; 180 [[L. Ed. 2d]] 408", "Prior": "Motion granted, unreported [https://www.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.pamd.59147/gov.uscourts.pamd.59147.190.0.pdf 3:05-CV-1422] ([[United States District Court for the Middle District of Pennsylvania|M.D. Pa.]] 2010); affirmed, 364 [[Federal Appendix|Fed. Appx.]] 749 ([[United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit|3d Cir.]] 2010); [[certiorari|cert.]] granted, {{ussc|562|960|2010|el=no}}.", "Subsequent": "Further remanded to the district court, unreported (3d Cir. August 2, 2011)", "Holding": "A petition must address a matter of public concern. Otherwise, a public employer is free to retaliate against the public employee, even if the employee won the grievance he filed and brought suit in federal court.<ref>{{cite web|title=Supreme Court scales back First Amendment's Petition Clause|url=http://secondcircuitcivilrights.blogspot.de/2011/06/supreme-court-scales-back-first.html|work=Second Circuit Civil Rights Blog|publisher=Second Circuit Civil Rights Blog|accessdate=6 October 2012|date=21 June 2012}}</ref> Third Circuit reversed and remanded.", "SCOTUS": "2010-2016", "Majority": "Kennedy", "JoinMajority": "Roberts, Ginsburg, Breyer, Alito, Sotomayor, Kagan", "Concurrence": "Thomas", "Concurrence/Dissent": "Scalia", "LawsApplied": "[[First Amendment to the United States Constitution|U.S. Const. amend. I]]"}}